  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: dd64eb842f3dd694bae8487ce6510215, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Creation of the World'
      title: The Creation of the World
      number: 1
      content: '  In the beginning, God created the heavens and the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The earth was without form and void, and darkness was over the face
        of the deep. And the Spirit of God was hovering over the face of the waters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And God said, \u201CLet there be light,\u201D and there was light. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And God saw that the light was good. And God separated the light
        from the darkness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'God called the light Day, and the darkness he called Night. And there
        was evening and there was morning, the first day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And God said, \u201CLet there be an expanse[[COMMENT(0)]] in the
        midst of the waters, and let it separate the waters from the waters.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '1:6 '
        content: Or ; also verses 7, 8, 14, 15, 17, 20
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And God made[[COMMENT(0)]] the expanse and separated the waters that
        were under the expanse from the waters that were above the expanse. And it
        was so. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:7 '
        content: Or ; also verse 16
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And God called the expanse Heaven.[[COMMENT(0)]] And there was evening
        and there was morning, the second day.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:8 '
        content: Or ; also verses 9, 14, 15, 17, 20, 26, 28, 30; 2:1
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And God said, \u201CLet the waters under the heavens be gathered
        together into one place, and let the dry land appear.\u201D And it was so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'God called the dry land Earth,[[COMMENT(0)]] and the waters that
        were gathered together he called Seas. And God saw that it was good.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:10 '
        content: Or ; also verses 11, 12, 22, 24, 25, 26, 28, 30; 2:1
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And God said, \u201CLet the earth sprout vegetation, plants[[COMMENT(0)]]
        yielding seed, and fruit trees bearing fruit in which is their seed, each
        according to its kind, on the earth.\u201D And it was so. "
      comments:
      - number: '1:11 '
        content: Or ; also verses 12, 29
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The earth brought forth vegetation, plants yielding seed according
        to their own kinds, and trees bearing fruit in which is their seed, each
        according to its kind. And God saw that it was good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And there was evening and there was morning, the third day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And God said, \u201CLet there be lights in the expanse of the heavens
        to separate the day from the night. And let them be for signs and for seasons,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and for days and years, "
      comments:
      - number: '1:14 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "and let them be lights in the expanse of the heavens to give light
        upon the earth.\u201D And it was so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And God made the two great lights\u2014the greater light to rule
        the day and the lesser light to rule the night\u2014and the stars. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And God set them in the expanse of the heavens to give light on the
        earth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'to rule over the day and over the night, and to separate the light
        from the darkness. And God saw that it was good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And there was evening and there was morning, the fourth day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And God said, \u201CLet the waters swarm with swarms of living creatures,
        and let birds[[COMMENT(0)]] fly above the earth across the expanse of the
        heavens.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '1:20 '
        content: "Or ; see Leviticus 11:19\u201320"
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So God created the great sea creatures and every living creature
        that moves, with which the waters swarm, according to their kinds, and every
        winged bird according to its kind. And God saw that it was good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And God blessed them, saying, \u201CBe fruitful and multiply and
        fill the waters in the seas, and let birds multiply on the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And there was evening and there was morning, the fifth day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And God said, \u201CLet the earth bring forth living creatures according
        to their kinds\u2014livestock and creeping things and beasts of the earth
        according to their kinds.\u201D And it was so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And God made the beasts of the earth according to their kinds and
        the livestock according to their kinds, and everything that creeps on the
        ground according to its kind. And God saw that it was good.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then God said, \u201CLet us make man[[COMMENT(0)]] in our image,
        after our likeness. And let them have dominion over the fish of the sea and
        over the birds of the heavens and over the livestock and over all the earth
        and over every creeping thing that creeps on the earth.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:26 '
        content: 'The Hebrew word for () is the generic term for mankind and becomes
          the proper name '
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So God created man in his own image,in the image of God he created
        him;  male and female he created them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And God blessed them. And God said to them, \u201CBe fruitful and
        multiply and fill the earth and subdue it, and have dominion over the fish
        of the sea and over the birds of the heavens and over every living thing
        that moves on the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And God said, \u201CBehold, I have given you every plant yielding
        seed that is on the face of all the earth, and every tree with seed in its
        fruit. You shall have them for food. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And to every beast of the earth and to every bird of the heavens
        and to everything that creeps on the earth, everything that has the breath
        of life, I have given every green plant for food.\u201D And it was so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: And God saw everything that he had made, and behold, it was very good.
        And there was evening and there was morning, the sixth day.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Seventh Day, God Rests'
      title: The Seventh Day, God Rests
      number: 1
      content: '  Thus the heavens and the earth were finished, and all the host
        of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And on the seventh day God finished his work that he had done, and
        he rested on the seventh day from all his work that he had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: The Creation of Man and Woman'
      title: The Creation of Man and Woman
      number: 3
      content: 'So God blessed the seventh day and made it holy, because on it God
        rested from all his work that he had done in creation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  These are the generationsof the heavens and the earth when they
        were created,in the day that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God made the
        earth and the heavens.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "When no bush of the field[[COMMENT(0)]] was yet in the land and no
        small plant of the field had yet sprung up\u2014for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        God had not caused it to rain on the land, and there was no man to work the
        ground, "
      comments:
      - number: '2:5 '
        content: Or Or ; also verse 6
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "and a mist[[COMMENT(0)]] was going up from the land and was watering
        the whole face of the ground\u2014 "
      comments:
      - number: '2:6 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God formed the man of dust from
        the ground and breathed into his nostrils the breath of life, and the man
        became a living creature. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God planted a garden in Eden,
        in the east, and there he put the man whom he had formed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And out of the ground the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God made to
        spring up every tree that is pleasant to the sight and good for food. The
        tree of life was in the midst of the garden, and the tree of the knowledge
        of good and evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'A river flowed out of Eden to water the garden, and there it divided
        and became four rivers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The name of the first is the Pishon. It is the one that flowed around
        the whole land of Havilah, where there is gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the gold of that land is good; bdellium and onyx stone are there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The name of the second river is the Gihon. It is the one that flowed
        around the whole land of Cush. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And the name of the third river is the Tigris, which flows east of
        Assyria. And the fourth river is the Euphrates.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God took the man and put him in the
        garden of Eden to work it and keep it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God commanded the man, saying,
        \u201CYou may surely eat of every tree of the garden, "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "but of the tree of the knowledge of good and evil you shall not eat,
        for in the day that you eat[[COMMENT(0)]] of it you shall surely die.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:17 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God said, \u201CIt is not good
        that the man should be alone; I will make him a helper fit for[[COMMENT(0)]]
        him.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '2:18 '
        content: Or ; also verse 20
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now out of the ground the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God had formed[[COMMENT(0)]]
        every beast of the field and every bird of the heavens and brought them to
        the man to see what he would call them. And whatever the man called every
        living creature, that was its name. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:19 '
        content: 'Or <span class="ChapterContent_bdit___RrVH">Lord</span>  '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The man gave names to all livestock and to the birds of the heavens
        and to every beast of the field. But for Adam[[COMMENT(0)]] there was not
        found a helper fit for him. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:20 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God caused a deep sleep to fall
        upon the man, and while he slept took one of his ribs and closed up its place
        with flesh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And the rib that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God had taken from
        the man he made[[COMMENT(0)]] into a woman and brought her to the man. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:22 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then the man said,\u201CThis at last is bone of my bonesand flesh
        of my flesh;she shall be called Woman,because she was taken out of Man.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:23 '
        content: The Hebrew words for () and () sound alike
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '  Therefore a man shall leave his father and his mother and hold
        fast to his wife, and they shall become one flesh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: And the man and his wife were both naked and were not ashamed.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Fall'
      title: The Fall
      number: 1
      content: "  Now the serpent was more crafty than any other beast of the field
        that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God had made.He said to the woman, \u201CDid
        God actually say, \u2018You[[COMMENT(0)]] shall not eat of any tree in the
        garden\u2019?\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '3:1 '
        content: "In Hebrew is plural in verses 1\u20135"
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the woman said to the serpent, \u201CWe may eat of the fruit
        of the trees in the garden, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "but God said, \u2018You shall not eat of the fruit of the tree that
        is in the midst of the garden, neither shall you touch it, lest you die.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But the serpent said to the woman, \u201CYou will not surely die. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For God knows that when you eat of it your eyes will be opened, and
        you will be like God, knowing good and evil.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So when the woman saw that the tree was good for food, and that it
        was a delight to the eyes, and that the tree was to be desired to make one
        wise,[[COMMENT(0)]] she took of its fruit and ate, and she also gave some
        to her husband who was with her, and he ate. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:6 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then the eyes of both were opened, and they knew that they were naked.
        And they sewed fig leaves together and made themselves loincloths.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And they heard the sound of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God walking
        in the garden in the cool[[COMMENT(0)]] of the day, and the man and his wife
        hid themselves from the presence of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God among
        the trees of the garden. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:8 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God called to the man and said
        to him, \u201CWhere are you?\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:9 '
        content: In Hebrew is singular in verses 9 and 11
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And he said, \u201CI heard the sound of you in the garden, and I
        was afraid, because I was naked, and I hid myself.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "He said, \u201CWho told you that you were naked? Have you eaten of
        the tree of which I commanded you not to eat?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The man said, \u201CThe woman whom you gave to be with me, she gave
        me fruit of the tree, and I ate.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God said to the woman, \u201CWhat
        is this that you have done?\u201D The woman said, \u201CThe serpent deceived
        me, and I ate.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God said to the serpent,\u201CBecause
        you have done this,cursed are you above all livestockand above all beasts
        of the field;on your belly you shall go,and dust you shall eatall the days
        of your life.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "I will put enmity between you and the woman,and between your offspring[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and her offspring;  he shall bruise your head,and you shall bruise his heel.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:15 '
        content: Hebrew ; so throughout Genesis
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "To the woman he said,\u201CI will surely multiply your pain in childbearing; 
        in pain you shall bring forth children.  Your desire shall be contrary to[[COMMENT(0)]]
        your husband,but he shall rule over you.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:16 '
        content: Or (see 4:7)
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And to Adam he said,\u201CBecause you have listened to the voice
        of your wifeand have eaten of the tree  of which I commanded you,\u2018You
        shall not eat of it,\u2019  cursed is the ground because of you;  in pain
        you shall eat of it all the days of your life;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'thorns and thistles it shall bring forth for you;and you shall eat
        the plants of the field.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "By the sweat of your faceyou shall eat bread,till you return to the
        ground,for out of it you were taken;  for you are dust,and to dust you shall
        return.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "The man called his wife\u2019s name Eve, because she was the mother
        of all living.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:20 '
        content: 'sounds like the Hebrew for and resembles the word for '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God made for Adam and for his
        wife garments of skins and clothed them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God said, \u201CBehold, the
        man has become like one of us in knowing good and evil. Now, lest he reach
        out his hand and take also of the tree of life and eat, and live forever\u2014\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'therefore the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God sent him out from the
        garden of Eden to work the ground from which he was taken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: He drove out the man, and at the east of the garden of Eden he placed
        the cherubim and a flaming sword that turned every way to guard the way to
        the tree of life.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Cain and Abel'
      title: Cain and Abel
      number: 1
      content: "  Now Adam knew Eve his wife, and she conceived and bore Cain, saying,
        \u201CI have gotten[[COMMENT(0)]] a man with the help of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '4:1 '
        content: 'sounds like the Hebrew for '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And again, she bore his brother Abel. Now Abel was a keeper of sheep,
        and Cain a worker of the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'In the course of time Cain brought to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        an offering of the fruit of the ground, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and Abel also brought of the firstborn of his flock and of their
        fat portions. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  had regard for Abel and
        his offering, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'but for Cain and his offering he had no regard. So Cain was very
        angry, and his face fell. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Cain, \u201CWhy are you angry,
        and why has your face fallen? "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "If you do well, will you not be accepted?[[COMMENT(0)]] And if you
        do not do well, sin is crouching at the door. Its desire is contrary to you,
        but you must rule over it.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:7 '
        content: 'Hebrew [of your face]?Or '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Cain spoke to Abel his brother.[[COMMENT(0)]] And when they were
        in the field, Cain rose up against his brother Abel and killed him. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:8 '
        content: 'Hebrew; Samaritan, Septuagint, Syriac, Vulgate add '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Cain, \u201CWhere is
        Abel your brother?\u201D He said, \u201CI do not know; am I my brother\u2019s
        keeper?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CWhat have you done?
        The voice of your brother\u2019s blood is crying to me from the ground. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And now you are cursed from the ground, which has opened its mouth
        to receive your brother\u2019s blood from your hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "When you work the ground, it shall no longer yield to you its strength.
        You shall be a fugitive and a wanderer on the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Cain said to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u201CMy punishment
        is greater than I can bear.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:13 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Behold, you have driven me today away from the ground, and from your
        face I shall be hidden. I shall be a fugitive and a wanderer on the earth,
        and whoever finds me will kill me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to him, \u201CNot so! If
        anyone kills Cain, vengeance shall be taken on him sevenfold.\u201D And the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  put a mark on Cain, lest any who found him should
        attack him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then Cain went away from the presence of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and settled in the land of Nod,[[COMMENT(0)]] east of Eden.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:16 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Cain knew his wife, and she conceived and bore Enoch. When he built
        a city, he called the name of the city after the name of his son, Enoch. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'To Enoch was born Irad, and Irad fathered Mehujael, and Mehujael
        fathered Methushael, and Methushael fathered Lamech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And Lamech took two wives. The name of the one was Adah, and the
        name of the other Zillah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Adah bore Jabal; he was the father of those who dwell in tents and
        have livestock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "His brother\u2019s name was Jubal; he was the father of all those
        who play the lyre and pipe. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Zillah also bore Tubal-cain; he was the forger of all instruments
        of bronze and iron. The sister of Tubal-cain was Naamah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Lamech said to his wives:\u201CAdah and Zillah, hear my voice;you
        wives of Lamech, listen to what I say:I have killed a man for wounding me,a
        young man for striking me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "  If Cain\u2019s revenge is sevenfold,then Lamech\u2019s is seventy-sevenfold.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And Adam knew his wife again, and she bore a son and called his name
        Seth, for she said, \u201CGod has appointed[[COMMENT(0)]] for me another
        offspring instead of Abel, for Cain killed him.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '4:25 '
        content: 'sounds like the Hebrew for '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: To Seth also a son was born, and he called his name Enosh. At that
        time people began to call upon the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Adam\u2019s Descendants to Noah"
      title: "Adam\u2019s Descendants to Noah"
      number: 1
      content: '  This is the book of the generations of Adam. When God created man,
        he made him in the likeness of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Male and female he created them, and he blessed them and named them
        Man[[COMMENT(0)]] when they were created. '
      comments:
      - number: '5:2 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When Adam had lived 130 years, he fathered a son in his own likeness,
        after his image, and named him Seth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The days of Adam after he fathered Seth were 800 years; and he had
        other sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Thus all the days that Adam lived were 930 years, and he died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When Seth had lived 105 years, he fathered Enosh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Seth lived after he fathered Enosh 807 years and had other sons and
        daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Thus all the days of Seth were 912 years, and he died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When Enosh had lived 90 years, he fathered Kenan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Enosh lived after he fathered Kenan 815 years and had other sons
        and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Thus all the days of Enosh were 905 years, and he died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When Kenan had lived 70 years, he fathered Mahalalel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Kenan lived after he fathered Mahalalel 840 years and had other sons
        and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Thus all the days of Kenan were 910 years, and he died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When Mahalalel had lived 65 years, he fathered Jared. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Mahalalel lived after he fathered Jared 830 years and had other sons
        and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Thus all the days of Mahalalel were 895 years, and he died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When Jared had lived 162 years, he fathered Enoch. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Jared lived after he fathered Enoch 800 years and had other sons
        and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Thus all the days of Jared were 962 years, and he died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'When Enoch had lived 65 years, he fathered Methuselah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Enoch walked with God[[COMMENT(0)]] after he fathered Methuselah
        300 years and had other sons and daughters. '
      comments:
      - number: '5:22 '
        content: Septuagint ; also verse 24
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Thus all the days of Enoch were 365 years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Enoch walked with God, and he was not,[[COMMENT(0)]]  for God took
        him.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:24 '
        content: 'Septuagint '
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'When Methuselah had lived 187 years, he fathered Lamech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Methuselah lived after he fathered Lamech 782 years and had other
        sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Thus all the days of Methuselah were 969 years, and he died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'When Lamech had lived 182 years, he fathered a son '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "and called his name Noah, saying, \u201COut of the ground that the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has cursed, this one shall bring us relief[[COMMENT(0)]]
        from our work and from the painful toil of our hands.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '5:29 '
        content: 'sounds like the Hebrew for '
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Lamech lived after he fathered Noah 595 years and had other sons
        and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Thus all the days of Lamech were 777 years, and he died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: After Noah was 500 years old, Noah fathered Shem, Ham, and Japheth.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Increasing Corruption on Earth'
      title: Increasing Corruption on Earth
      number: 1
      content: '  When man began to multiply on the face of the land and daughters
        were born to them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'the sons of God saw that the daughters of man were attractive. And
        they took as their wives any they chose. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CMy Spirit shall
        not abide in[[COMMENT(0)]] man forever, for he is flesh: his days shall be
        120 years.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '6:3 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The Nephilim[[COMMENT(0)]] were on the earth in those days, and also
        afterward, when the sons of God came in to the daughters of man and they
        bore children to them. These were the mighty men who were of old, the men
        of renown.  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:4 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> saw that the wickedness of man
        was great in the earth, and that every intention of the thoughts of his heart
        was only evil continually. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> regretted that he had made man
        on the earth, and it grieved him to his heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CI will blot out man
        whom I have created from the face of the land, man and animals and creeping
        things and birds of the heavens, for I am sorry that I have made them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Noah and the Flood'
      title: Noah and the Flood
      number: 8
      content: 'But Noah found favor in the eyes of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'These are the generations of Noah. Noah was a righteous man, blameless
        in his generation. Noah walked with God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Noah had three sons, Shem, Ham, and Japheth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now the earth was corrupt in God\u2019s sight, and the earth was
        filled with violence. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And God saw the earth, and behold, it was corrupt, for all flesh
        had corrupted their way on the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And God said to Noah, \u201CI have determined to make an end of all
        flesh,[[COMMENT(0)]] for the earth is filled with violence through them.
        Behold, I will destroy them with the earth. "
      comments:
      - number: '6:13 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Make yourself an ark of gopher wood.[[COMMENT(0)]] Make rooms in
        the ark, and cover it inside and out with pitch. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:14 '
        content: An unknown kind of tree; transliterated from Hebrew
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'This is how you are to make it: the length of the ark 300 cubits,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        its breadth 50 cubits, and its height 30 cubits. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:15 '
        content: A was about 18 inches or 45 centimeters
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Make a roof[[COMMENT(0)]] for the ark, and finish it to a cubit above,
        and set the door of the ark in its side. Make it with lower, second, and
        third decks. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:16 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For behold, I will bring a flood of waters upon the earth to destroy
        all flesh in which is the breath of life under heaven. Everything that is
        on the earth shall die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But I will establish my covenant with you, and you shall come into
        the ark, you, your sons, your wife, and your sons\u2019 wives with you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And of every living thing of all flesh, you shall bring two of every
        sort into the ark to keep them alive with you. They shall be male and female. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Of the birds according to their kinds, and of the animals according
        to their kinds, of every creeping thing of the ground, according to its kind,
        two of every sort shall come in to you to keep them alive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Also take with you every sort of food that is eaten, and store it
        up. It shall serve as food for you and for them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Noah did this; he did all that God commanded him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "  Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Noah, \u201CGo into
        the ark, you and all your household, for I have seen that you are righteous
        before me in this generation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Take with you seven pairs of all clean animals,[[COMMENT(0)]] the
        male and his mate, and a pair of the animals that are not clean, the male
        and his mate, '
      comments:
      - number: '7:2 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and seven pairs[[COMMENT(0)]] of the birds of the heavens also, male
        and female, to keep their offspring alive on the face of all the earth. '
      comments:
      - number: '7:3 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For in seven days I will send rain on the earth forty days and forty
        nights, and every living thing[[COMMENT(0)]] that I have made I will blot
        out from the face of the ground.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '7:4 '
        content: Hebrew ; also verse 23
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Noah did all that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded
        him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Noah was six hundred years old when the flood of waters came upon
        the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Noah and his sons and his wife and his sons\u2019 wives with
        him went into the ark to escape the waters of the flood. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Of clean animals, and of animals that are not clean, and of birds,
        and of everything that creeps on the ground, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'two and two, male and female, went into the ark with Noah, as God
        had commanded Noah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And after seven days the waters of the flood came upon the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "In the six hundredth year of Noah\u2019s life, in the second month,
        on the seventeenth day of the month, on that day all the fountains of the
        great deep burst forth, and the windows of the heavens were opened. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And rain fell upon the earth forty days and forty nights. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "On the very same day Noah and his sons, Shem and Ham and Japheth,
        and Noah\u2019s wife and the three wives of his sons with them entered the
        ark, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'they and every beast, according to its kind, and all the livestock
        according to their kinds, and every creeping thing that creeps on the earth,
        according to its kind, and every bird, according to its kind, every winged
        creature. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'They went into the ark with Noah, two and two of all flesh in which
        there was the breath of life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And those that entered, male and female of all flesh, went in as
        God had commanded him. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> shut him in.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The flood continued forty days on the earth. The waters increased
        and bore up the ark, and it rose high above the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The waters prevailed and increased greatly on the earth, and the
        ark floated on the face of the waters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And the waters prevailed so mightily on the earth that all the high
        mountains under the whole heaven were covered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The waters prevailed above the mountains, covering them fifteen cubits[[COMMENT(0)]]
        deep. '
      comments:
      - number: '7:20 '
        content: A was about 18 inches or 45 centimeters
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And all flesh died that moved on the earth, birds, livestock, beasts,
        all swarming creatures that swarm on the earth, and all mankind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Everything on the dry land in whose nostrils was the breath of life
        died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'He blotted out every living thing that was on the face of the ground,
        man and animals and creeping things and birds of the heavens. They were blotted
        out from the earth. Only Noah was left, and those who were with him in the
        ark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: And the waters prevailed on the earth 150 days.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Flood Subsides'
      title: The Flood Subsides
      number: 1
      content: '  But God remembered Noah and all the beasts and all the livestock
        that were with him in the ark. And God made a wind blow over the earth, and
        the waters subsided. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The fountains of the deep and the windows of the heavens were closed,
        the rain from the heavens was restrained, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and the waters receded from the earth continually. At the end of
        150 days the waters had abated, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and in the seventh month, on the seventeenth day of the month, the
        ark came to rest on the mountains of Ararat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the waters continued to abate until the tenth month; in the tenth
        month, on the first day of the month, the tops of the mountains were seen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'At the end of forty days Noah opened the window of the ark that he
        had made '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and sent forth a raven. It went to and fro until the waters were
        dried up from the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then he sent forth a dove from him, to see if the waters had subsided
        from the face of the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But the dove found no place to set her foot, and she returned to
        him to the ark, for the waters were still on the face of the whole earth.
        So he put out his hand and took her and brought her into the ark with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He waited another seven days, and again he sent forth the dove out
        of the ark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the dove came back to him in the evening, and behold, in her
        mouth was a freshly plucked olive leaf. So Noah knew that the waters had
        subsided from the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then he waited another seven days and sent forth the dove, and she
        did not return to him anymore.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'In the six hundred and first year, in the first month, the first
        day of the month, the waters were dried from off the earth. And Noah removed
        the covering of the ark and looked, and behold, the face of the ground was
        dry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'In the second month, on the twenty-seventh day of the month, the
        earth had dried out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then God said to Noah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CGo out from the ark, you and your wife, and your sons and your
        sons\u2019 wives with you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Bring out with you every living thing that is with you of all flesh\u2014birds
        and animals and every creeping thing that creeps on the earth\u2014that they
        may swarm on the earth, and be fruitful and multiply on the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So Noah went out, and his sons and his wife and his sons\u2019 wives
        with him. "
      comments: []
    - name: "19: God\u2019s Covenant with Noah"
      title: "God\u2019s Covenant with Noah"
      number: 19
      content: 'Every beast, every creeping thing, and every bird, everything that
        moves on the earth, went out by families from the ark.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then Noah built an altar to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and took
        some of every clean animal and some of every clean bird and offered burnt
        offerings on the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> smelled the pleasing aroma,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said in his heart, \u201CI will never again
        curse[[COMMENT(0)]] the ground because of man, for the intention of man\u2019s
        heart is evil from his youth. Neither will I ever again strike down every
        living creature as I have done. "
      comments:
      - number: '8:21 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "While the earth remains, seedtime and harvest, cold and heat, summer
        and winter, day and night, shall not cease.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "  And God blessed Noah and his sons and said to them, \u201CBe fruitful
        and multiply and fill the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The fear of you and the dread of you shall be upon every beast of
        the earth and upon every bird of the heavens, upon everything that creeps
        on the ground and all the fish of the sea. Into your hand they are delivered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Every moving thing that lives shall be food for you. And as I gave
        you the green plants, I give you everything. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But you shall not eat flesh with its life, that is, its blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And for your lifeblood I will require a reckoning: from every beast
        I will require it and from man. From his fellow man I will require a reckoning
        for the life of man.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "  \u201CWhoever sheds the blood of man,by man shall his blood be
        shed,  for God made man in his own image.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And you,[[COMMENT(0)]] be fruitful and multiply, increase greatly
        on the earth and multiply in it.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:7 '
        content: In Hebrew is plural
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then God said to Noah and to his sons with him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CBehold, I establish my covenant with you and your offspring
        after you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and with every living creature that is with you, the birds, the livestock,
        and every beast of the earth with you, as many as came out of the ark; it
        is for every beast of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "I establish my covenant with you, that never again shall all flesh
        be cut off by the waters of the flood, and never again shall there be a flood
        to destroy the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And God said, \u201CThis is the sign of the covenant that I make
        between me and you and every living creature that is with you, for all future
        generations: "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I have set my bow in the cloud, and it shall be a sign of the covenant
        between me and the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'When I bring clouds over the earth and the bow is seen in the clouds, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'I will remember my covenant that is between me and you and every
        living creature of all flesh. And the waters shall never again become a flood
        to destroy all flesh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When the bow is in the clouds, I will see it and remember the everlasting
        covenant between God and every living creature of all flesh that is on the
        earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "17: Noah\u2019s Descendants"
      title: "Noah\u2019s Descendants"
      number: 17
      content: "God said to Noah, \u201CThis is the sign of the covenant that I have
        established between me and all flesh that is on the earth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The sons of Noah who went forth from the ark were Shem, Ham, and
        Japheth. (Ham was the father of Canaan.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'These three were the sons of Noah, and from these the people of the
        whole earth were dispersed.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:19 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Noah began to be a man of the soil, and he planted a vineyard.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:20 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He drank of the wine and became drunk and lay uncovered in his tent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Ham, the father of Canaan, saw the nakedness of his father and
        told his two brothers outside. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then Shem and Japheth took a garment, laid it on both their shoulders,
        and walked backward and covered the nakedness of their father. Their faces
        were turned backward, and they did not see their father\u2019s nakedness. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When Noah awoke from his wine and knew what his youngest son had
        done to him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "he said,  \u201CCursed be Canaan;  a servant of servants shall he
        be to his brothers.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "He also said,\u201CBlessed be the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the
        God of Shem;and let Canaan be his servant.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "May God enlarge Japheth,[[COMMENT(0)]]and let him dwell in the tents
        of Shem,and let Canaan be his servant.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:27 '
        content: 'sounds like the Hebrew for '
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'After the flood Noah lived 350 years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: All the days of Noah were 950 years, and he died.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Nations Descended from Noah'
      title: Nations Descended from Noah
      number: 1
      content: '  These are the generations of the sons of Noah, Shem, Ham, and Japheth.
        Sons were born to them after the flood.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  The sons of Japheth: Gomer, Magog, Madai, Javan, Tubal, Meshech,
        and Tiras. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The sons of Gomer: Ashkenaz, Riphath, and Togarmah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The sons of Javan: Elishah, Tarshish, Kittim, and Dodanim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'From these the coastland peoples spread in their lands, each with
        his own language, by their clans, in their nations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  The sons of Ham: Cush, Egypt, Put, and Canaan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The sons of Cush: Seba, Havilah, Sabtah, Raamah, and Sabteca. The
        sons of Raamah: Sheba and Dedan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Cush fathered Nimrod; he was the first on earth to be a mighty man.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:8 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He was a mighty hunter before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. Therefore
        it is said, \u201CLike Nimrod a mighty hunter before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The beginning of his kingdom was Babel, Erech, Accad, and Calneh,
        in the land of Shinar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'From that land he went into Assyria and built Nineveh, Rehoboth-Ir,
        Calah, and '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Resen between Nineveh and Calah; that is the great city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Egypt fathered Ludim, Anamim, Lehabim, Naphtuhim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Pathrusim, Casluhim (from whom[[COMMENT(0)]] the Philistines came),
        and Caphtorim.  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:14 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  Canaan fathered Sidon his firstborn and Heth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'and the Jebusites, the Amorites, the Girgashites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'the Hivites, the Arkites, the Sinites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'the Arvadites, the Zemarites, and the Hamathites. Afterward the clans
        of the Canaanites dispersed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And the territory of the Canaanites extended from Sidon in the direction
        of Gerar as far as Gaza, and in the direction of Sodom, Gomorrah, Admah,
        and Zeboiim, as far as Lasha. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'These are the sons of Ham, by their clans, their languages, their
        lands, and their nations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'To Shem also, the father of all the children of Eber, the elder brother
        of Japheth, children were born. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The sons of Shem: Elam, Asshur, Arpachshad, Lud, and Aram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The sons of Aram: Uz, Hul, Gether, and Mash. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Arpachshad fathered Shelah; and Shelah fathered Eber. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "To Eber were born two sons: the name of the one was Peleg,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        for in his days the earth was divided, and his brother\u2019s name was Joktan. "
      comments:
      - number: '10:25 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Joktan fathered Almodad, Sheleph, Hazarmaveth, Jerah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Hadoram, Uzal, Diklah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Obal, Abimael, Sheba, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Ophir, Havilah, and Jobab; all these were the sons of Joktan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The territory in which they lived extended from Mesha in the direction
        of Sephar to the hill country of the east. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'These are the sons of Shem, by their clans, their languages, their
        lands, and their nations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: These are the clans of the sons of Noah, according to their genealogies,
        in their nations, and from these the nations spread abroad on the earth after
        the flood.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Tower of Babel'
      title: The Tower of Babel
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the whole earth had one language and the same words. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And as people migrated from the east, they found a plain in the land
        of Shinar and settled there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And they said to one another, \u201CCome, let us make bricks, and
        burn them thoroughly.\u201D And they had brick for stone, and bitumen for
        mortar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then they said, \u201CCome, let us build ourselves a city and a tower
        with its top in the heavens, and let us make a name for ourselves, lest we
        be dispersed over the face of the whole earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came down to see the city and
        the tower, which the children of man had built. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CBehold, they are
        one people, and they have all one language, and this is only the beginning
        of what they will do. And nothing that they propose to do will now be impossible
        for them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Come, let us go down and there confuse their language, so that they
        may not understand one another\u2019s speech.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> dispersed them from there over
        the face of all the earth, and they left off building the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: "9: Shem\u2019s Descendants"
      title: "Shem\u2019s Descendants"
      number: 9
      content: 'Therefore its name was called Babel, because there the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        confused[[COMMENT(0)]] the language of all the earth. And from there the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> dispersed them over the face of all the earth.  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:9 '
        content: 'sounds like the Hebrew for '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  These are the generations of Shem. When Shem was 100 years old,
        he fathered Arpachshad two years after the flood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Shem lived after he fathered Arpachshad 500 years and had other
        sons and daughters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When Arpachshad had lived 35 years, he fathered Shelah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Arpachshad lived after he fathered Shelah 403 years and had other
        sons and daughters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'When Shelah had lived 30 years, he fathered Eber. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Shelah lived after he fathered Eber 403 years and had other sons
        and daughters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'When Eber had lived 34 years, he fathered Peleg. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And Eber lived after he fathered Peleg 430 years and had other sons
        and daughters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When Peleg had lived 30 years, he fathered Reu. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And Peleg lived after he fathered Reu 209 years and had other sons
        and daughters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'When Reu had lived 32 years, he fathered Serug. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And Reu lived after he fathered Serug 207 years and had other sons
        and daughters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'When Serug had lived 30 years, he fathered Nahor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And Serug lived after he fathered Nahor 200 years and had other sons
        and daughters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When Nahor had lived 29 years, he fathered Terah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And Nahor lived after he fathered Terah 119 years and had other sons
        and daughters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "26: Terah\u2019s Descendants"
      title: "Terah\u2019s Descendants"
      number: 26
      content: 'When Terah had lived 70 years, he fathered Abram, Nahor, and Haran.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now these are the generations of Terah. Terah fathered Abram, Nahor,
        and Haran; and Haran fathered Lot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Haran died in the presence of his father Terah in the land of his
        kindred, in Ur of the Chaldeans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And Abram and Nahor took wives. The name of Abram\u2019s wife was
        Sarai, and the name of Nahor\u2019s wife, Milcah, the daughter of Haran the
        father of Milcah and Iscah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Now Sarai was barren; she had no child.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Terah took Abram his son and Lot the son of Haran, his grandson,
        and Sarai his daughter-in-law, his son Abram\u2019s wife, and they went forth
        together from Ur of the Chaldeans to go into the land of Canaan, but when
        they came to Haran, they settled there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: The days of Terah were 205 years, and Terah died in Haran.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Call of Abram'
      title: The Call of Abram
      number: 1
      content: "  Now the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said[[COMMENT(0)]] to Abram,
        \u201CGo from your country and your kindred and your father\u2019s house
        to the land that I will show you. "
      comments:
      - number: '12:1 '
        content: 'Or Or '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And I will make of you a great nation, and I will bless you and make
        your name great, so that you will be a blessing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "I will bless those who bless you, and him who dishonors you I will
        curse, and in you all the families of the earth shall be blessed.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:3 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So Abram went, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had told him, and
        Lot went with him. Abram was seventy-five years old when he departed from
        Haran. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And Abram took Sarai his wife, and Lot his brother\u2019s son, and
        all their possessions that they had gathered, and the people that they had
        acquired in Haran, and they set out to go to the land of Canaan. When they
        came to the land of Canaan, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Abram passed through the land to the place at Shechem, to the oak[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of Moreh. At that time the Canaanites were in the land. '
      comments:
      - number: '12:6 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> appeared to Abram and said,
        \u201CTo your offspring I will give this land.\u201D So he built there an
        altar to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, who had appeared to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'From there he moved to the hill country on the east of Bethel and
        pitched his tent, with Bethel on the west and Ai on the east. And there he
        built an altar to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and called upon the name
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Abram and Sarai in Egypt'
      title: Abram and Sarai in Egypt
      number: 9
      content: 'And Abram journeyed on, still going toward the Negeb.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now there was a famine in the land. So Abram went down to Egypt to
        sojourn there, for the famine was severe in the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "When he was about to enter Egypt, he said to Sarai his wife, \u201CI
        know that you are a woman beautiful in appearance, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "and when the Egyptians see you, they will say, \u2018This is his
        wife.\u2019 Then they will kill me, but they will let you live. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Say you are my sister, that it may go well with me because of you,
        and that my life may be spared for your sake.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'When Abram entered Egypt, the Egyptians saw that the woman was very
        beautiful. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And when the princes of Pharaoh saw her, they praised her to Pharaoh.
        And the woman was taken into Pharaoh\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And for her sake he dealt well with Abram; and he had sheep, oxen,
        male donkeys, male servants, female servants, female donkeys, and camels.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  afflicted Pharaoh and his house
        with great plagues because of Sarai, Abram\u2019s wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So Pharaoh called Abram and said, \u201CWhat is this you have done
        to me? Why did you not tell me that she was your wife? "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Why did you say, \u2018She is my sister,\u2019 so that I took her
        for my wife? Now then, here is your wife; take her, and go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: And Pharaoh gave men orders concerning him, and they sent him away
        with his wife and all that he had.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Abram and Lot Separate'
      title: Abram and Lot Separate
      number: 1
      content: '  So Abram went up from Egypt, he and his wife and all that he had,
        and Lot with him, into the Negeb.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  Now Abram was very rich in livestock, in silver, and in gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And he journeyed on from the Negeb as far as Bethel to the place
        where his tent had been at the beginning, between Bethel and Ai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'to the place where he had made an altar at the first. And there Abram
        called upon the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Lot, who went with Abram, also had flocks and herds and tents, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'so that the land could not support both of them dwelling together;
        for their possessions were so great that they could not dwell together, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "and there was strife between the herdsmen of Abram\u2019s livestock
        and the herdsmen of Lot\u2019s livestock. At that time the Canaanites and
        the Perizzites were dwelling in the land.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Abram said to Lot, \u201CLet there be no strife between you
        and me, and between your herdsmen and my herdsmen, for we are kinsmen.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:8 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Is not the whole land before you? Separate yourself from me. If you
        take the left hand, then I will go to the right, or if you take the right
        hand, then I will go to the left.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Lot lifted up his eyes and saw that the Jordan Valley was well
        watered everywhere like the garden of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, like
        the land of Egypt, in the direction of Zoar. (This was before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        destroyed Sodom and Gomorrah.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So Lot chose for himself all the Jordan Valley, and Lot journeyed
        east. Thus they separated from each other. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Abram settled in the land of Canaan, while Lot settled among the
        cities of the valley and moved his tent as far as Sodom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now the men of Sodom were wicked, great sinners against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Abram, after Lot had separated
        from him, \u201CLift up your eyes and look from the place where you are,
        northward and southward and eastward and westward, "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'for all the land that you see I will give to you and to your offspring
        forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I will make your offspring as the dust of the earth, so that if one
        can count the dust of the earth, your offspring also can be counted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Arise, walk through the length and the breadth of the land, for I
        will give it to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: So Abram moved his tent and came and settled by the oaks[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of Mamre, which are at Hebron, and there he built an altar to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
      comments:
      - number: '13:18 '
        content: 'Or '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Abram Rescues Lot'
      title: Abram Rescues Lot
      number: 1
      content: '  In the days of Amraphel king of Shinar, Arioch king of Ellasar,
        Chedorlaomer king of Elam, and Tidal king of Goiim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'these kings made war with Bera king of Sodom, Birsha king of Gomorrah,
        Shinab king of Admah, Shemeber king of Zeboiim, and the king of Bela (that
        is, Zoar). '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And all these joined forces in the Valley of Siddim (that is, the
        Salt Sea). '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Twelve years they had served Chedorlaomer, but in the thirteenth
        year they rebelled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'In the fourteenth year Chedorlaomer and the kings who were with him
        came and defeated the Rephaim in Ashteroth-karnaim, the Zuzim in Ham, the
        Emim in Shaveh-kiriathaim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and the Horites in their hill country of Seir as far as El-paran
        on the border of the wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then they turned back and came to En-mishpat (that is, Kadesh) and
        defeated all the country of the Amalekites, and also the Amorites who were
        dwelling in Hazazon-tamar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the king of Sodom, the king of Gomorrah, the king of Admah,
        the king of Zeboiim, and the king of Bela (that is, Zoar) went out, and they
        joined battle in the Valley of Siddim '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'with Chedorlaomer king of Elam, Tidal king of Goiim, Amraphel king
        of Shinar, and Arioch king of Ellasar, four kings against five. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now the Valley of Siddim was full of bitumen pits, and as the kings
        of Sodom and Gomorrah fled, some fell into them, and the rest fled to the
        hill country. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So the enemy took all the possessions of Sodom and Gomorrah, and
        all their provisions, and went their way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "They also took Lot, the son of Abram\u2019s brother, who was dwelling
        in Sodom, and his possessions, and went their way.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then one who had escaped came and told Abram the Hebrew, who was
        living by the oaks[[COMMENT(0)]] of Mamre the Amorite, brother of Eshcol
        and of Aner. These were allies of Abram. '
      comments:
      - number: '14:13 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'When Abram heard that his kinsman had been taken captive, he led
        forth his trained men, born in his house, 318 of them, and went in pursuit
        as far as Dan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And he divided his forces against them by night, he and his servants,
        and defeated them and pursued them to Hobah, north of Damascus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Abram Blessed by Melchizedek'
      title: Abram Blessed by Melchizedek
      number: 16
      content: 'Then he brought back all the possessions, and also brought back his
        kinsman Lot with his possessions, and the women and the people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "After his return from the defeat of Chedorlaomer and the kings who
        were with him, the king of Sodom went out to meet him at the Valley of Shaveh
        (that is, the King\u2019s Valley). "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And Melchizedek king of Salem brought out bread and wine. (He was
        priest of God Most High.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And he blessed him and said,  \u201CBlessed be Abram by God Most
        High,  Possessor[[COMMENT(0)]] of heaven and earth;  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:19 '
        content: Or ; also verse 22
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "and blessed be God Most High,who has delivered your enemies into
        your hand!\u201DAnd Abram gave him a tenth of everything. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And the king of Sodom said to Abram, \u201CGive me the persons, but
        take the goods for yourself.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But Abram said to the king of Sodom, \u201CI have lifted my hand[[COMMENT(0)]]
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, God Most High, Possessor of heaven and
        earth, "
      comments:
      - number: '14:22 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "that I would not take a thread or a sandal strap or anything that
        is yours, lest you should say, \u2018I have made Abram rich.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "I will take nothing but what the young men have eaten, and the share
        of the men who went with me. Let Aner, Eshcol, and Mamre take their share.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Covenant with Abram"
      title: "God\u2019s Covenant with Abram"
      number: 1
      content: "  After these things the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        came to Abram in a vision: \u201CFear not, Abram, I am your shield; your
        reward shall be very great.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "But Abram said, \u201CO Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>, what will
        you give me, for I continue[[COMMENT(0)]] childless, and the heir of my house
        is Eliezer of Damascus?\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '15:2 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And Abram said, \u201CBehold, you have given me no offspring, and
        a member of my household will be my heir.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And behold, the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to him:
        \u201CThis man shall not be your heir; your very own son[[COMMENT(0)]] shall
        be your heir.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '15:4 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And he brought him outside and said, \u201CLook toward heaven, and
        number the stars, if you are able to number them.\u201D Then he said to him,
        \u201CSo shall your offspring be.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he believed the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and he counted it
        to him as righteousness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And he said to him, \u201CI am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who
        brought you out from Ur of the Chaldeans to give you this land to possess.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But he said, \u201CO Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>, how am I to
        know that I shall possess it?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He said to him, \u201CBring me a heifer three years old, a female
        goat three years old, a ram three years old, a turtledove, and a young pigeon.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And he brought him all these, cut them in half, and laid each half
        over against the other. But he did not cut the birds in half. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And when birds of prey came down on the carcasses, Abram drove them
        away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'As the sun was going down, a deep sleep fell on Abram. And behold,
        dreadful and great darkness fell upon him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Abram, \u201CKnow for
        certain that your offspring will be sojourners in a land that is not theirs
        and will be servants there, and they will be afflicted for four hundred years. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But I will bring judgment on the nation that they serve, and afterward
        they shall come out with great possessions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'As for you, you shall go to your fathers in peace; you shall be buried
        in a good old age. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And they shall come back here in the fourth generation, for the iniquity
        of the Amorites is not yet complete.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'When the sun had gone down and it was dark, behold, a smoking fire
        pot and a flaming torch passed between these pieces. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "On that day the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> made a covenant with
        Abram, saying, \u201CTo your offspring I give[[COMMENT(0)]] this land, from
        the river of Egypt to the great river, the river Euphrates, "
      comments:
      - number: '15:18 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'the land of the Kenites, the Kenizzites, the Kadmonites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'the Hittites, the Perizzites, the Rephaim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "the Amorites, the Canaanites, the Girgashites and the Jebusites.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Sarai and Hagar'
      title: Sarai and Hagar
      number: 1
      content: "    Now Sarai, Abram\u2019s wife, had borne him no children. She
        had a female Egyptian servant whose name was Hagar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Sarai said to Abram, \u201CBehold now, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has prevented me from bearing children. Go in to my servant; it may be that
        I shall obtain children[[COMMENT(0)]] by her.\u201D And Abram listened to
        the voice of Sarai. "
      comments:
      - number: '16:2 '
        content: 'Hebrew , which sounds like the Hebrew for '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So, after Abram had lived ten years in the land of Canaan, Sarai,
        Abram\u2019s wife, took Hagar the Egyptian, her servant, and gave her to
        Abram her husband as a wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And he went in to Hagar, and she conceived. And when she saw that
        she had conceived, she looked with contempt on her mistress.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:4 '
        content: Hebrew ; similarly in verse 5
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And Sarai said to Abram, \u201CMay the wrong done to me be on you!
        I gave my servant to your embrace, and when she saw that she had conceived,
        she looked on me with contempt. May the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> judge
        between you and me!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But Abram said to Sarai, \u201CBehold, your servant is in your power;
        do to her as you please.\u201D Then Sarai dealt harshly with her, and she
        fled from her.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> found her by a spring
        of water in the wilderness, the spring on the way to Shur. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And he said, \u201CHagar, servant of Sarai, where have you come from
        and where are you going?\u201D She said, \u201CI am fleeing from my mistress
        Sarai.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to her, \u201CReturn
        to your mistress and submit to her.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> also said to her, \u201CI
        will surely multiply your offspring so that they cannot be numbered for multitude.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to her,\u201CBehold,
        you are pregnantand shall bear a son.You shall call his name Ishmael,[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has listened to your affliction.  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:11 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "He shall be a wild donkey of a man,his hand against everyoneand everyone\u2019s
        hand against him,and he shall dwell over against all his kinsmen.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So she called the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who spoke
        to her, \u201CYou are a God of seeing,\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]] for she said,
        \u201CTruly here I have seen him who looks after me.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:13 '
        content: 'Or Hebrew or '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore the well was called Beer-lahai-roi;[[COMMENT(0)]] it lies
        between Kadesh and Bered.  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:14 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Hagar bore Abram a son, and Abram called the name of his son,
        whom Hagar bore, Ishmael. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Abram was eighty-six years old when Hagar bore Ishmael to Abram.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Abraham and the Covenant of Circumcision'
      title: Abraham and the Covenant of Circumcision
      number: 1
      content: "  When Abram was ninety-nine years old the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        appeared to Abram and said to him, \u201CI am God Almighty;[[COMMENT(0)]]
        walk before me, and be blameless, "
      comments:
      - number: '17:1 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "that I may make my covenant between me and you, and may multiply
        you greatly.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Abram fell on his face. And God said to him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CBehold, my covenant is with you, and you shall be the father
        of a multitude of nations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'No longer shall your name be called Abram,[[COMMENT(0)]] but your
        name shall be Abraham,  for I have made you the father of a multitude of
        nations. '
      comments:
      - number: '17:5 '
        content: 'means means '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I will make you exceedingly fruitful, and I will make you into nations,
        and kings shall come from you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And I will establish my covenant between me and you and your offspring
        after you throughout their generations for an everlasting covenant, to be
        God to you and to your offspring after you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And I will give to you and to your offspring after you the land of
        your sojournings, all the land of Canaan, for an everlasting possession,
        and I will be their God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And God said to Abraham, \u201CAs for you, you shall keep my covenant,
        you and your offspring after you throughout their generations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'This is my covenant, which you shall keep, between me and you and
        your offspring after you: Every male among you shall be circumcised. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'You shall be circumcised in the flesh of your foreskins, and it shall
        be a sign of the covenant between me and you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He who is eight days old among you shall be circumcised. Every male
        throughout your generations, whether born in your house or bought with your
        money from any foreigner who is not of your offspring, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'both he who is born in your house and he who is bought with your
        money, shall surely be circumcised. So shall my covenant be in your flesh
        an everlasting covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: "14: Isaac\u2019s Birth Promised"
      title: "Isaac\u2019s Birth Promised"
      number: 14
      content: "Any uncircumcised male who is not circumcised in the flesh of his
        foreskin shall be cut off from his people; he has broken my covenant.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And God said to Abraham, \u201CAs for Sarai your wife, you shall
        not call her name Sarai, but Sarah[[COMMENT(0)]] shall be her name. "
      comments:
      - number: '17:15 '
        content: 'and mean '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "I will bless her, and moreover, I will give[[COMMENT(0)]] you a son
        by her. I will bless her, and she shall become nations; kings of peoples
        shall come from her.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '17:16 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Abraham fell on his face and laughed and said to himself, \u201CShall
        a child be born to a man who is a hundred years old? Shall Sarah, who is
        ninety years old, bear a child?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Abraham said to God, \u201COh that Ishmael might live before
        you!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "God said, \u201CNo, but Sarah your wife shall bear you a son, and
        you shall call his name Isaac.[[COMMENT(0)]] I will establish my covenant
        with him as an everlasting covenant for his offspring after him. "
      comments:
      - number: '17:19 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'As for Ishmael, I have heard you; behold, I have blessed him and
        will make him fruitful and multiply him greatly. He shall father twelve princes,
        and I will make him into a great nation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But I will establish my covenant with Isaac, whom Sarah shall bear
        to you at this time next year.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'When he had finished talking with him, God went up from Abraham. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then Abraham took Ishmael his son and all those born in his house
        or bought with his money, every male among the men of Abraham\u2019s house,
        and he circumcised the flesh of their foreskins that very day, as God had
        said to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Abraham was ninety-nine years old when he was circumcised in the
        flesh of his foreskin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And Ishmael his son was thirteen years old when he was circumcised
        in the flesh of his foreskin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'That very day Abraham and his son Ishmael were circumcised. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: And all the men of his house, those born in the house and those bought
        with money from a foreigner, were circumcised with him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> appeared to him by the oaks[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of Mamre, as he sat at the door of his tent in the heat of the day. '
      comments:
      - number: '18:1 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He lifted up his eyes and looked, and behold, three men were standing
        in front of him. When he saw them, he ran from the tent door to meet them
        and bowed himself to the earth '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and said, \u201CO Lord,[[COMMENT(0)]] if I have found favor in your
        sight, do not pass by your servant. "
      comments:
      - number: '18:3 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Let a little water be brought, and wash your feet, and rest yourselves
        under the tree, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "while I bring a morsel of bread, that you may refresh yourselves,
        and after that you may pass on\u2014since you have come to your servant.\u201D
        So they said, \u201CDo as you have said.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Abraham went quickly into the tent to Sarah and said, \u201CQuick!
        Three seahs[[COMMENT(0)]] of fine flour! Knead it, and make cakes.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '18:6 '
        content: A was about 7 quarts or 7.3 liters
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And Abraham ran to the herd and took a calf, tender and good, and
        gave it to a young man, who prepared it quickly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then he took curds and milk and the calf that he had prepared, and
        set it before them. And he stood by them under the tree while they ate.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "They said to him, \u201CWhere is Sarah your wife?\u201D And he said,
        \u201CShe is in the tent.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CI will surely return
        to you about this time next year, and Sarah your wife shall have a son.\u201D
        And Sarah was listening at the tent door behind him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now Abraham and Sarah were old, advanced in years. The way of women
        had ceased to be with Sarah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So Sarah laughed to herself, saying, \u201CAfter I am worn out, and
        my lord is old, shall I have pleasure?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Abraham, \u201CWhy did Sarah
        laugh and say, \u2018Shall I indeed bear a child, now that I am old?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Is anything too hard[[COMMENT(0)]] for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?
        At the appointed time I will return to you, about this time next year, and
        Sarah shall have a son.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '18:14 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But Sarah denied it,[[COMMENT(0)]] saying, \u201CI did not laugh,\u201D
        for she was afraid. He said, \u201CNo, but you did laugh.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '18:15 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then the men set out from there, and they looked down toward Sodom.
        And Abraham went with them to set them on their way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CShall I hide from Abraham
        what I am about to do, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'seeing that Abraham shall surely become a great and mighty nation,
        and all the nations of the earth shall be blessed in him? '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "For I have chosen[[COMMENT(0)]] him, that he may command his children
        and his household after him to keep the way of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        by doing righteousness and justice, so that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        may bring to Abraham what he has promised him.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '18:19 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CBecause the outcry
        against Sodom and Gomorrah is great and their sin is very grave, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Abraham Intercedes for Sodom'
      title: Abraham Intercedes for Sodom
      number: 21
      content: "I will go down to see whether they have done altogether[[COMMENT(0)]]
        according to the outcry that has come to me. And if not, I will know.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '18:21 '
        content: 'Or ; Hebrew '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  So the men turned from there and went toward Sodom, but Abraham
        still stood before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then Abraham drew near and said, \u201CWill you indeed sweep away
        the righteous with the wicked? "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Suppose there are fifty righteous within the city. Will you then
        sweep away the place and not spare it for the fifty righteous who are in
        it? '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Far be it from you to do such a thing, to put the righteous to death
        with the wicked, so that the righteous fare as the wicked! Far be that from
        you! Shall not the Judge of all the earth do what is just?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CIf I find at Sodom
        fifty righteous in the city, I will spare the whole place for their sake.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Abraham answered and said, \u201CBehold, I have undertaken to speak
        to the Lord, I who am but dust and ashes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Suppose five of the fifty righteous are lacking. Will you destroy
        the whole city for lack of five?\u201D And he said, \u201CI will not destroy
        it if I find forty-five there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Again he spoke to him and said, \u201CSuppose forty are found there.\u201D
        He answered, \u201CFor the sake of forty I will not do it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then he said, \u201COh let not the Lord be angry, and I will speak.
        Suppose thirty are found there.\u201D He answered, \u201CI will not do it,
        if I find thirty there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "He said, \u201CBehold, I have undertaken to speak to the Lord. Suppose
        twenty are found there.\u201D He answered, \u201CFor the sake of twenty I
        will not destroy it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then he said, \u201COh let not the Lord be angry, and I will speak
        again but this once. Suppose ten are found there.\u201D He answered, \u201CFor
        the sake of ten I will not destroy it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> went his way, when he had finished
        speaking to Abraham, and Abraham returned to his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Rescues Lot'
      title: God Rescues Lot
      number: 1
      content: '  The two angels came to Sodom in the evening, and Lot was sitting
        in the gate of Sodom. When Lot saw them, he rose to meet them and bowed himself
        with his face to the earth '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and said, \u201CMy lords, please turn aside to your servant\u2019s
        house and spend the night and wash your feet. Then you may rise up early
        and go on your way.\u201D They said, \u201CNo; we will spend the night in
        the town square.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But he pressed them strongly; so they turned aside to him and entered
        his house. And he made them a feast and baked unleavened bread, and they
        ate.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But before they lay down, the men of the city, the men of Sodom,
        both young and old, all the people to the last man, surrounded the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And they called to Lot, \u201CWhere are the men who came to you tonight?
        Bring them out to us, that we may know them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Lot went out to the men at the entrance, shut the door after him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "and said, \u201CI beg you, my brothers, do not act so wickedly. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Behold, I have two daughters who have not known any man. Let me bring
        them out to you, and do to them as you please. Only do nothing to these men,
        for they have come under the shelter of my roof.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But they said, \u201CStand back!\u201D And they said, \u201CThis
        fellow came to sojourn, and he has become the judge! Now we will deal worse
        with you than with them.\u201D Then they pressed hard against the man Lot,
        and drew near to break the door down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But the men reached out their hands and brought Lot into the house
        with them and shut the door. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And they struck with blindness the men who were at the entrance of
        the house, both small and great, so that they wore themselves out groping
        for the door.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the men said to Lot, \u201CHave you anyone else here? Sons-in-law,
        sons, daughters, or anyone you have in the city, bring them out of the place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "For we are about to destroy this place, because the outcry against
        its people has become great before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has sent us to destroy it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So Lot went out and said to his sons-in-law, who were to marry his
        daughters, \u201CUp! Get out of this place, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is about to destroy the city.\u201D But he seemed to his sons-in-law to be
        jesting.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "As morning dawned, the angels urged Lot, saying, \u201CUp! Take your
        wife and your two daughters who are here, lest you be swept away in the punishment
        of the city.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But he lingered. So the men seized him and his wife and his two daughters
        by the hand, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> being merciful to him, and they
        brought him out and set him outside the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And as they brought them out, one said, \u201CEscape for your life.
        Do not look back or stop anywhere in the valley. Escape to the hills, lest
        you be swept away.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Lot said to them, \u201COh, no, my lords. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Behold, your servant has found favor in your sight, and you have
        shown me great kindness in saving my life. But I cannot escape to the hills,
        lest the disaster overtake me and I die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Behold, this city is near enough to flee to, and it is a little one.
        Let me escape there\u2014is it not a little one?\u2014and my life will be
        saved!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "He said to him, \u201CBehold, I grant you this favor also, that I
        will not overthrow the city of which you have spoken. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: God Destroys Sodom'
      title: God Destroys Sodom
      number: 22
      content: "Escape there quickly, for I can do nothing till you arrive there.\u201D
        Therefore the name of the city was called Zoar.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:22 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The sun had risen on the earth when Lot came to Zoar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> rained on Sodom and Gomorrah
        sulfur and fire from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> out of heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And he overthrew those cities, and all the valley, and all the inhabitants
        of the cities, and what grew on the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But Lot\u2019s wife, behind him, looked back, and she became a pillar
        of salt.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And Abraham went early in the morning to the place where he had stood
        before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And he looked down toward Sodom and Gomorrah and toward all the land
        of the valley, and he looked and, behold, the smoke of the land went up like
        the smoke of a furnace.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: Lot and His Daughters'
      title: Lot and His Daughters
      number: 29
      content: 'So it was that, when God destroyed the cities of the valley, God
        remembered Abraham and sent Lot out of the midst of the overthrow when he
        overthrew the cities in which Lot had lived.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Now Lot went up out of Zoar and lived in the hills with his two daughters,
        for he was afraid to live in Zoar. So he lived in a cave with his two daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And the firstborn said to the younger, \u201COur father is old, and
        there is not a man on earth to come in to us after the manner of all the
        earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Come, let us make our father drink wine, and we will lie with him,
        that we may preserve offspring from our father.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'So they made their father drink wine that night. And the firstborn
        went in and lay with her father. He did not know when she lay down or when
        she arose.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "The next day, the firstborn said to the younger, \u201CBehold, I
        lay last night with my father. Let us make him drink wine tonight also. Then
        you go in and lie with him, that we may preserve offspring from our father.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'So they made their father drink wine that night also. And the younger
        arose and lay with him, and he did not know when she lay down or when she
        arose. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Thus both the daughters of Lot became pregnant by their father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'The firstborn bore a son and called his name Moab.[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        He is the father of the Moabites to this day. '
      comments:
      - number: '19:37 '
        content: 'sounds like the Hebrew for '
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: The younger also bore a son and called his name Ben-ammi.[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        He is the father of the Ammonites to this day.
      comments:
      - number: '19:38 '
        content: 'means '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Abraham and Abimelech'
      title: Abraham and Abimelech
      number: 1
      content: '  From there Abraham journeyed toward the territory of the Negeb
        and lived between Kadesh and Shur; and he sojourned in Gerar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Abraham said of Sarah his wife, \u201CShe is my sister.\u201D
        And Abimelech king of Gerar sent and took Sarah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But God came to Abimelech in a dream by night and said to him, \u201CBehold,
        you are a dead man because of the woman whom you have taken, for she is a
        man\u2019s wife.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Now Abimelech had not approached her. So he said, \u201CLord, will
        you kill an innocent people? "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Did he not himself say to me, \u2018She is my sister\u2019? And she
        herself said, \u2018He is my brother.\u2019 In the integrity of my heart
        and the innocence of my hands I have done this.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then God said to him in the dream, \u201CYes, I know that you have
        done this in the integrity of your heart, and it was I who kept you from
        sinning against me. Therefore I did not let you touch her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now then, return the man\u2019s wife, for he is a prophet, so that
        he will pray for you, and you shall live. But if you do not return her, know
        that you shall surely die, you and all who are yours.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So Abimelech rose early in the morning and called all his servants
        and told them all these things. And the men were very much afraid. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Abimelech called Abraham and said to him, \u201CWhat have you
        done to us? And how have I sinned against you, that you have brought on me
        and my kingdom a great sin? You have done to me things that ought not to
        be done.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Abimelech said to Abraham, \u201CWhat did you see, that you did
        this thing?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Abraham said, \u201CI did it because I thought, \u2018There is no
        fear of God at all in this place, and they will kill me because of my wife.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Besides, she is indeed my sister, the daughter of my father though
        not the daughter of my mother, and she became my wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And when God caused me to wander from my father\u2019s house, I said
        to her, \u2018This is the kindness you must do me: at every place to which
        we come, say of me, \u201CHe is my brother.\u201D\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then Abimelech took sheep and oxen, and male servants and female
        servants, and gave them to Abraham, and returned Sarah his wife to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And Abimelech said, \u201CBehold, my land is before you; dwell where
        it pleases you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "To Sarah he said, \u201CBehold, I have given your brother a thousand
        pieces of silver. It is a sign of your innocence in the eyes of all[[COMMENT(0)]]
        who are with you, and before everyone you are vindicated.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '20:16 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then Abraham prayed to God, and God healed Abimelech, and also healed
        his wife and female slaves so that they bore children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  had closed all the wombs of
        the house of Abimelech because of Sarah, Abraham\u2019s wife."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Birth of Isaac'
      title: The Birth of Isaac
      number: 1
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  visited Sarah as he had said,
        and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> did to Sarah as he had promised. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Sarah conceived and bore Abraham a son in his old age at the
        time of which God had spoken to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Abraham called the name of his son who was born to him, whom Sarah
        bore him, Isaac.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '21:3 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And Abraham circumcised his son Isaac when he was eight days old,
        as God had commanded him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Abraham was a hundred years old when his son Isaac was born to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Sarah said, \u201CGod has made laughter for me; everyone who
        hears will laugh over me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: God Protects Hagar and Ishmael'
      title: God Protects Hagar and Ishmael
      number: 7
      content: "And she said, \u201CWho would have said to Abraham that Sarah would
        nurse children? Yet I have borne him a son in his old age.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the child grew and was weaned. And Abraham made a great feast
        on the day that Isaac was weaned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But Sarah saw the son of Hagar the Egyptian, whom she had borne to
        Abraham, laughing.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '21:9 '
        content: 'Possibly '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So she said to Abraham, \u201CCast out this slave woman with her
        son, for the son of this slave woman shall not be heir with my son Isaac.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the thing was very displeasing to Abraham on account of his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But God said to Abraham, \u201CBe not displeased because of the boy
        and because of your slave woman. Whatever Sarah says to you, do as she tells
        you, for through Isaac shall your offspring be named. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And I will make a nation of the son of the slave woman also, because
        he is your offspring.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So Abraham rose early in the morning and took bread and a skin of
        water and gave it to Hagar, putting it on her shoulder, along with the child,
        and sent her away. And she departed and wandered in the wilderness of Beersheba.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When the water in the skin was gone, she put the child under one
        of the bushes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then she went and sat down opposite him a good way off, about the
        distance of a bowshot, for she said, \u201CLet me not look on the death of
        the child.\u201D And as she sat opposite him, she lifted up her voice and
        wept. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And God heard the voice of the boy, and the angel of God called to
        Hagar from heaven and said to her, \u201CWhat troubles you, Hagar? Fear not,
        for God has heard the voice of the boy where he is. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Up! Lift up the boy, and hold him fast with your hand, for I will
        make him into a great nation.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then God opened her eyes, and she saw a well of water. And she went
        and filled the skin with water and gave the boy a drink. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And God was with the boy, and he grew up. He lived in the wilderness
        and became an expert with the bow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: A Treaty with Abimelech'
      title: A Treaty with Abimelech
      number: 21
      content: 'He lived in the wilderness of Paran, and his mother took a wife for
        him from the land of Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "At that time Abimelech and Phicol the commander of his army said
        to Abraham, \u201CGod is with you in all that you do. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Now therefore swear to me here by God that you will not deal falsely
        with me or with my descendants or with my posterity, but as I have dealt
        kindly with you, so you will deal with me and with the land where you have
        sojourned.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And Abraham said, \u201CI will swear.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "When Abraham reproved Abimelech about a well of water that Abimelech\u2019s
        servants had seized, "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Abimelech said, \u201CI do not know who has done this thing; you
        did not tell me, and I have not heard of it until today.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So Abraham took sheep and oxen and gave them to Abimelech, and the
        two men made a covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Abraham set seven ewe lambs of the flock apart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And Abimelech said to Abraham, \u201CWhat is the meaning of these
        seven ewe lambs that you have set apart?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "He said, \u201CThese seven ewe lambs you will take from my hand,
        that this[[COMMENT(0)]] may be a witness for me that I dug this well.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '21:30 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Therefore that place was called Beersheba,[[COMMENT(0)]] because
        there both of them swore an oath. '
      comments:
      - number: '21:31 '
        content: 'means or '
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'So they made a covenant at Beersheba. Then Abimelech and Phicol the
        commander of his army rose up and returned to the land of the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Abraham planted a tamarisk tree in Beersheba and called there on
        the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the Everlasting God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: And Abraham sojourned many days in the land of the Philistines.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Sacrifice of Isaac'
      title: The Sacrifice of Isaac
      number: 1
      content: "  After these things God tested Abraham and said to him, \u201CAbraham!\u201D
        And he said, \u201CHere I am.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He said, \u201CTake your son, your only son Isaac, whom you love,
        and go to the land of Moriah, and offer him there as a burnt offering on
        one of the mountains of which I shall tell you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So Abraham rose early in the morning, saddled his donkey, and took
        two of his young men with him, and his son Isaac. And he cut the wood for
        the burnt offering and arose and went to the place of which God had told
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'On the third day Abraham lifted up his eyes and saw the place from
        afar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Abraham said to his young men, \u201CStay here with the donkey;
        I and the boy[[COMMENT(0)]] will go over there and worship and come again
        to you.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '22:5 '
        content: Or ; also verse 12
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Abraham took the wood of the burnt offering and laid it on Isaac
        his son. And he took in his hand the fire and the knife. So they went both
        of them together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Isaac said to his father Abraham, \u201CMy father!\u201D And
        he said, \u201CHere I am, my son.\u201D He said, \u201CBehold, the fire and
        the wood, but where is the lamb for a burnt offering?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Abraham said, \u201CGod will provide for himself the lamb for a burnt
        offering, my son.\u201D So they went both of them together.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When they came to the place of which God had told him, Abraham built
        the altar there and laid the wood in order and bound Isaac his son and laid
        him on the altar, on top of the wood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then Abraham reached out his hand and took the knife to slaughter
        his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> called to him from
        heaven and said, \u201CAbraham, Abraham!\u201D And he said, \u201CHere I
        am.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "He said, \u201CDo not lay your hand on the boy or do anything to
        him, for now I know that you fear God, seeing you have not withheld your
        son, your only son, from me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Abraham lifted up his eyes and looked, and behold, behind him
        was a ram, caught in a thicket by his horns. And Abraham went and took the
        ram and offered it up as a burnt offering instead of his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So Abraham called the name of that place, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will provide\u201D;[[COMMENT(0)]] as it is said to this day, \u201COn the
        mount of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> it shall be provided.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:14 '
        content: 'Or Or '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> called to Abraham
        a second time from heaven '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "and said, \u201CBy myself I have sworn, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        because you have done this and have not withheld your son, your only son, "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'I will surely bless you, and I will surely multiply your offspring
        as the stars of heaven and as the sand that is on the seashore. And your
        offspring shall possess the gate of his[[COMMENT(0)]] enemies, '
      comments:
      - number: '22:17 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "and in your offspring shall all the nations of the earth be blessed,
        because you have obeyed my voice.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So Abraham returned to his young men, and they arose and went together
        to Beersheba. And Abraham lived at Beersheba.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Now after these things it was told to Abraham, \u201CBehold, Milcah
        also has borne children to your brother Nahor: "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Uz his firstborn, Buz his brother, Kemuel the father of Aram, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Chesed, Hazo, Pildash, Jidlaph, and Bethuel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "(Bethuel fathered Rebekah.) These eight Milcah bore to Nahor, Abraham\u2019s
        brother. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Moreover, his concubine, whose name was Reumah, bore Tebah, Gaham,
        Tahash, and Maacah.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Sarah\u2019s Death and Burial"
      title: "Sarah\u2019s Death and Burial"
      number: 1
      content: '  Sarah lived 127 years; these were the years of the life of Sarah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Sarah died at Kiriath-arba (that is, Hebron) in the land of Canaan,
        and Abraham went in to mourn for Sarah and to weep for her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Abraham rose up from before his dead and said to the Hittites,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:3 '
        content: Hebrew ; also verses 5, 7, 10, 16, 18, 20
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CI am a sojourner and foreigner among you; give me property
        among you for a burying place, that I may bury my dead out of my sight.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The Hittites answered Abraham, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CHear us, my lord; you are a prince of God[[COMMENT(0)]] among
        us. Bury your dead in the choicest of our tombs. None of us will withhold
        from you his tomb to hinder you from burying your dead.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '23:6 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Abraham rose and bowed to the Hittites, the people of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CIf you are willing that I should bury
        my dead out of my sight, hear me and entreat for me Ephron the son of Zohar, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "that he may give me the cave of Machpelah, which he owns; it is at
        the end of his field. For the full price let him give it to me in your presence
        as property for a burying place.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now Ephron was sitting among the Hittites, and Ephron the Hittite
        answered Abraham in the hearing of the Hittites, of all who went in at the
        gate of his city, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CNo, my lord, hear me: I give you the field, and I give you
        the cave that is in it. In the sight of the sons of my people I give it to
        you. Bury your dead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then Abraham bowed down before the people of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And he said to Ephron in the hearing of the people of the land, \u201CBut
        if you will, hear me: I give the price of the field. Accept it from me, that
        I may bury my dead there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Ephron answered Abraham, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CMy lord, listen to me: a piece of land worth four hundred shekels[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of silver, what is that between you and me? Bury your dead.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '23:15 '
        content: A was about 2/5 ounce or 11 grams
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Abraham listened to Ephron, and Abraham weighed out for Ephron the
        silver that he had named in the hearing of the Hittites, four hundred shekels
        of silver, according to the weights current among the merchants.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So the field of Ephron in Machpelah, which was to the east of Mamre,
        the field with the cave that was in it and all the trees that were in the
        field, throughout its whole area, was made over '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'to Abraham as a possession in the presence of the Hittites, before
        all who went in at the gate of his city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'After this, Abraham buried Sarah his wife in the cave of the field
        of Machpelah east of Mamre (that is, Hebron) in the land of Canaan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: The field and the cave that is in it were made over to Abraham as
        property for a burying place by the Hittites.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Isaac and Rebekah'
      title: Isaac and Rebekah
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Abraham was old, well advanced in years. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        had blessed Abraham in all things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Abraham said to his servant, the oldest of his household, who
        had charge of all that he had, \u201CPut your hand under my thigh, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'that I may make you swear by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the
        God of heaven and God of the earth, that you will not take a wife for my
        son from the daughters of the Canaanites, among whom I dwell, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "but will go to my country and to my kindred, and take a wife for
        my son Isaac.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The servant said to him, \u201CPerhaps the woman may not be willing
        to follow me to this land. Must I then take your son back to the land from
        which you came?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Abraham said to him, \u201CSee to it that you do not take my son
        back there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of heaven, who took me from
        my father\u2019s house and from the land of my kindred, and who spoke to
        me and swore to me, \u2018To your offspring I will give this land,\u2019
        he will send his angel before you, and you shall take a wife for my son from
        there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But if the woman is not willing to follow you, then you will be free
        from this oath of mine; only you must not take my son back there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So the servant put his hand under the thigh of Abraham his master
        and swore to him concerning this matter.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then the servant took ten of his master\u2019s camels and departed,
        taking all sorts of choice gifts from his master; and he arose and went to
        Mesopotamia[[COMMENT(0)]] to the city of Nahor. "
      comments:
      - number: '24:10 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And he made the camels kneel down outside the city by the well of
        water at the time of evening, the time when women go out to draw water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And he said, \u201CO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, God of my master
        Abraham, please grant me success today and show steadfast love to my master
        Abraham. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Behold, I am standing by the spring of water, and the daughters of
        the men of the city are coming out to draw water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Let the young woman to whom I shall say, \u2018Please let down your
        jar that I may drink,\u2019 and who shall say, \u2018Drink, and I will water
        your camels\u2019\u2014let her be the one whom you have appointed for your
        servant Isaac. By this[[COMMENT(0)]] I shall know that you have shown steadfast
        love to my master.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '24:14 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Before he had finished speaking, behold, Rebekah, who was born to
        Bethuel the son of Milcah, the wife of Nahor, Abraham\u2019s brother, came
        out with her water jar on her shoulder. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The young woman was very attractive in appearance, a maiden[[COMMENT(0)]]
        whom no man had known. She went down to the spring and filled her jar and
        came up. '
      comments:
      - number: '24:16 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then the servant ran to meet her and said, \u201CPlease give me a
        little water to drink from your jar.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "She said, \u201CDrink, my lord.\u201D And she quickly let down her
        jar upon her hand and gave him a drink. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "When she had finished giving him a drink, she said, \u201CI will
        draw water for your camels also, until they have finished drinking.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So she quickly emptied her jar into the trough and ran again to the
        well to draw water, and she drew for all his camels. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The man gazed at her in silence to learn whether the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had prospered his journey or not.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'When the camels had finished drinking, the man took a gold ring weighing
        a half shekel,[[COMMENT(0)]] and two bracelets for her arms weighing ten
        gold shekels, '
      comments:
      - number: '24:22 '
        content: A was about 2/5 ounce or 11 grams
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "and said, \u201CPlease tell me whose daughter you are. Is there room
        in your father\u2019s house for us to spend the night?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "She said to him, \u201CI am the daughter of Bethuel the son of Milcah,
        whom she bore to Nahor.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "She added, \u201CWe have plenty of both straw and fodder, and room
        to spend the night.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The man bowed his head and worshiped the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "and said, \u201CBlessed be the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God
        of my master Abraham, who has not forsaken his steadfast love and his faithfulness
        toward my master. As for me, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  has led me
        in the way to the house of my master\u2019s kinsmen.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then the young woman ran and told her mother\u2019s household about
        these things.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Rebekah had a brother whose name was Laban. Laban ran out toward
        the man, to the spring. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "As soon as he saw the ring and the bracelets on his sister\u2019s
        arms, and heard the words of Rebekah his sister, \u201CThus the man spoke
        to me,\u201D he went to the man. And behold, he was standing by the camels
        at the spring. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "He said, \u201CCome in, O blessed of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        Why do you stand outside? For I have prepared the house and a place for the
        camels.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'So the man came to the house and unharnessed the camels, and gave
        straw and fodder to the camels, and there was water to wash his feet and
        the feet of the men who were with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then food was set before him to eat. But he said, \u201CI will not
        eat until I have said what I have to say.\u201D He said, \u201CSpeak on.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "So he said, \u201CI am Abraham\u2019s servant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  has greatly blessed my master, and
        he has become great. He has given him flocks and herds, silver and gold,
        male servants and female servants, camels and donkeys. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And Sarah my master\u2019s wife bore a son to my master when she
        was old, and to him he has given all that he has. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "My master made me swear, saying, \u2018You shall not take a wife
        for my son from the daughters of the Canaanites, in whose land I dwell, "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "but you shall go to my father\u2019s house and to my clan and take
        a wife for my son.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "I said to my master, \u2018Perhaps the woman will not follow me.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "But he said to me, \u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, before
        whom I have walked, will send his angel with you and prosper your way. You
        shall take a wife for my son from my clan and from my father\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Then you will be free from my oath, when you come to my clan. And
        if they will not give her to you, you will be free from my oath.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "\u201CI came today to the spring and said, \u2018O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of my master Abraham, if now you are prospering the way that I go, "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "behold, I am standing by the spring of water. Let the virgin who
        comes out to draw water, to whom I shall say, \u201CPlease give me a little
        water from your jar to drink,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "and who will say to me, \u201CDrink, and I will draw for your camels
        also,\u201D let her be the woman whom the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has
        appointed for my master\u2019s son.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "\u201CBefore I had finished speaking in my heart, behold, Rebekah
        came out with her water jar on her shoulder, and she went down to the spring
        and drew water. I said to her, \u2018Please let me drink.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "She quickly let down her jar from her shoulder and said, \u2018Drink,
        and I will give your camels drink also.\u2019 So I drank, and she gave the
        camels drink also. "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "Then I asked her, \u2018Whose daughter are you?\u2019 She said, \u2018The
        daughter of Bethuel, Nahor\u2019s son, whom Milcah bore to him.\u2019 So
        I put the ring on her nose and the bracelets on her arms. "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "Then I bowed my head and worshiped the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and blessed the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of my master Abraham,
        who had led me by the right way[[COMMENT(0)]] to take the daughter of my
        master\u2019s kinsman for his son. "
      comments:
      - number: '24:48 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "Now then, if you are going to show steadfast love and faithfulness
        to my master, tell me; and if not, tell me, that I may turn to the right
        hand or to the left.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "Then Laban and Bethuel answered and said, \u201CThe thing has come
        from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>; we cannot speak to you bad or good. "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "Behold, Rebekah is before you; take her and go, and let her be the
        wife of your master\u2019s son, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has spoken.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "When Abraham\u2019s servant heard their words, he bowed himself to
        the earth before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'And the servant brought out jewelry of silver and of gold, and garments,
        and gave them to Rebekah. He also gave to her brother and to her mother costly
        ornaments. '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: "And he and the men who were with him ate and drank, and they spent
        the night there. When they arose in the morning, he said, \u201CSend me away
        to my master.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: "Her brother and her mother said, \u201CLet the young woman remain
        with us a while, at least ten days; after that she may go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "But he said to them, \u201CDo not delay me, since the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has prospered my way. Send me away that I may go to my master.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: "They said, \u201CLet us call the young woman and ask her.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "And they called Rebekah and said to her, \u201CWill you go with this
        man?\u201D She said, \u201CI will go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: "So they sent away Rebekah their sister and her nurse, and Abraham\u2019s
        servant and his men. "
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: "And they blessed Rebekah and said to her,\u201COur sister, may you
        becomethousands of ten thousands,and may your offspring possessthe gate of
        those who hate him!\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '24:60 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: 'Then Rebekah and her young women arose and rode on the camels and
        followed the man. Thus the servant took Rebekah and went his way.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'Now Isaac had returned from Beer-lahai-roi and was dwelling in the
        Negeb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'And Isaac went out to meditate in the field toward evening. And he
        lifted up his eyes and saw, and behold, there were camels coming. '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: 'And Rebekah lifted up her eyes, and when she saw Isaac, she dismounted
        from the camel '
      comments: []
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: "and said to the servant, \u201CWho is that man, walking in the field
        to meet us?\u201D The servant said, \u201CIt is my master.\u201D So she took
        her veil and covered herself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: 'And the servant told Isaac all the things that he had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '67: '
      title: 
      number: 67
      content: "Then Isaac brought her into the tent of Sarah his mother and took
        Rebekah, and she became his wife, and he loved her. So Isaac was comforted
        after his mother\u2019s death."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Abraham\u2019s Death and His Descendants"
      title: "Abraham\u2019s Death and His Descendants"
      number: 1
      content: '  Abraham took another wife, whose name was Keturah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'She bore him Zimran, Jokshan, Medan, Midian, Ishbak, and Shuah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Jokshan fathered Sheba and Dedan. The sons of Dedan were Asshurim,
        Letushim, and Leummim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The sons of Midian were Ephah, Epher, Hanoch, Abida, and Eldaah.
        All these were the children of Keturah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Abraham gave all he had to Isaac. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But to the sons of his concubines Abraham gave gifts, and while he
        was still living he sent them away from his son Isaac, eastward to the east
        country.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "These are the days of the years of Abraham\u2019s life, 175 years. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Abraham breathed his last and died in a good old age, an old man
        and full of years, and was gathered to his people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Isaac and Ishmael his sons buried him in the cave of Machpelah, in
        the field of Ephron the son of Zohar the Hittite, east of Mamre, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'the field that Abraham purchased from the Hittites. There Abraham
        was buried, with Sarah his wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'After the death of Abraham, God blessed Isaac his son. And Isaac
        settled at Beer-lahai-roi.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "These are the generations of Ishmael, Abraham\u2019s son, whom Hagar
        the Egyptian, Sarah\u2019s servant, bore to Abraham. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'These are the names of the sons of Ishmael, named in the order of
        their birth: Nebaioth, the firstborn of Ishmael; and Kedar, Adbeel, Mibsam, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Mishma, Dumah, Massa, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Hadad, Tema, Jetur, Naphish, and Kedemah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'These are the sons of Ishmael and these are their names, by their
        villages and by their encampments, twelve princes according to their tribes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '(These are the years of the life of Ishmael: 137 years. He breathed
        his last and died, and was gathered to his people.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: The Birth of Esau and Jacob'
      title: The Birth of Esau and Jacob
      number: 18
      content: 'They settled from Havilah to Shur, which is opposite Egypt in the
        direction of Assyria. He settled[[COMMENT(0)]] over against all his kinsmen.  '
      comments:
      - number: '25:18 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "These are the generations of Isaac, Abraham\u2019s son: Abraham fathered
        Isaac, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'and Isaac was forty years old when he took Rebekah, the daughter
        of Bethuel the Aramean of Paddan-aram, the sister of Laban the Aramean, to
        be his wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And Isaac prayed to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> for his wife,
        because she was barren. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> granted his prayer,
        and Rebekah his wife conceived. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "The children struggled together within her, and she said, \u201CIf
        it is thus, why is this happening to me?\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]] So she went
        to inquire of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments:
      - number: '25:22 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to her,  \u201CTwo nations
        are in your womb,and two peoples from within you[[COMMENT(0)]] shall be divided; 
        the one shall be stronger than the other,  the older shall serve the younger.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '25:23 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When her days to give birth were completed, behold, there were twins
        in her womb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The first came out red, all his body like a hairy cloak, so they
        called his name Esau. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Afterward his brother came out with his hand holding Esau\u2019s
        heel, so his name was called Jacob.[[COMMENT(0)]] Isaac was sixty years old
        when she bore them.  "
      comments:
      - number: '25:26 '
        content: 'means , or '
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'When the boys grew up, Esau was a skillful hunter, a man of the field,
        while Jacob was a quiet man, dwelling in tents. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: Esau Sells His Birthright'
      title: Esau Sells His Birthright
      number: 28
      content: 'Isaac loved Esau because he ate of his game, but Rebekah loved Jacob.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Once when Jacob was cooking stew, Esau came in from the field, and
        he was exhausted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And Esau said to Jacob, \u201CLet me eat some of that red stew, for
        I am exhausted!\u201D (Therefore his name was called Edom.[[COMMENT(0)]]) "
      comments:
      - number: '25:30 '
        content: 'sounds like the Hebrew for '
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Jacob said, \u201CSell me your birthright now.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Esau said, \u201CI am about to die; of what use is a birthright to
        me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Jacob said, \u201CSwear to me now.\u201D So he swore to him and sold
        his birthright to Jacob. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: Then Jacob gave Esau bread and lentil stew, and he ate and drank and
        rose and went his way. Thus Esau despised his birthright.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Promise to Isaac"
      title: "God\u2019s Promise to Isaac"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now there was a famine in the land, besides the former famine that
        was in the days of Abraham. And Isaac went to Gerar to Abimelech king of
        the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> appeared to him and said, \u201CDo
        not go down to Egypt; dwell in the land of which I shall tell you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Sojourn in this land, and I will be with you and will bless you,
        for to you and to your offspring I will give all these lands, and I will
        establish the oath that I swore to Abraham your father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I will multiply your offspring as the stars of heaven and will give
        to your offspring all these lands. And in your offspring all the nations
        of the earth shall be blessed, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Isaac and Abimelech'
      title: Isaac and Abimelech
      number: 5
      content: "because Abraham obeyed my voice and kept my charge, my commandments,
        my statutes, and my laws.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Isaac settled in Gerar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When the men of the place asked him about his wife, he said, \u201CShe
        is my sister,\u201D for he feared to say, \u201CMy wife,\u201D thinking,
        \u201Clest the men of the place should kill me because of Rebekah,\u201D
        because she was attractive in appearance. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When he had been there a long time, Abimelech king of the Philistines
        looked out of a window and saw Isaac laughing with[[COMMENT(0)]] Rebekah
        his wife. '
      comments:
      - number: '26:8 '
        content: Hebrew may suggest an intimate relationship
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Abimelech called Isaac and said, \u201CBehold, she is your wife.
        How then could you say, \u2018She is my sister\u2019?\u201D Isaac said to
        him, \u201CBecause I thought, \u2018Lest I die because of her.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Abimelech said, \u201CWhat is this you have done to us? One of the
        people might easily have lain with your wife, and you would have brought
        guilt upon us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So Abimelech warned all the people, saying, \u201CWhoever touches
        this man or his wife shall surely be put to death.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And Isaac sowed in that land and reaped in the same year a hundredfold.
        The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  blessed him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and the man became rich, and gained more and more until he became
        very wealthy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He had possessions of flocks and herds and many servants, so that
        the Philistines envied him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "(Now the Philistines had stopped and filled with earth all the wells
        that his father\u2019s servants had dug in the days of Abraham his father.) "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And Abimelech said to Isaac, \u201CGo away from us, for you are much
        mightier than we.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So Isaac departed from there and encamped in the Valley of Gerar
        and settled there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And Isaac dug again the wells of water that had been dug in the days
        of Abraham his father, which the Philistines had stopped after the death
        of Abraham. And he gave them the names that his father had given them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But when Isaac\u2019s servants dug in the valley and found there
        a well of spring water, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "the herdsmen of Gerar quarreled with Isaac\u2019s herdsmen, saying,
        \u201CThe water is ours.\u201D So he called the name of the well Esek,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        because they contended with him. "
      comments:
      - number: '26:20 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then they dug another well, and they quarreled over that also, so
        he called its name Sitnah.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '26:21 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And he moved from there and dug another well, and they did not quarrel
        over it. So he called its name Rehoboth,[[COMMENT(0)]] saying, \u201CFor
        now the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has made room for us, and we shall be
        fruitful in the land.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '26:22 '
        content: 'means , or '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'From there he went up to Beersheba. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> appeared to him the same night
        and said, \u201CI am the God of Abraham your father. Fear not, for I am with
        you and will bless you and multiply your offspring for my servant Abraham\u2019s
        sake.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So he built an altar there and called upon the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and pitched his tent there. And there Isaac\u2019s servants dug a well.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'When Abimelech went to him from Gerar with Ahuzzath his adviser and
        Phicol the commander of his army, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Isaac said to them, \u201CWhy have you come to me, seeing that you
        hate me and have sent me away from you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "They said, \u201CWe see plainly that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has been with you. So we said, let there be a sworn pact between us, between
        you and us, and let us make a covenant with you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "that you will do us no harm, just as we have not touched you and
        have done to you nothing but good and have sent you away in peace. You are
        now the blessed of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'So he made them a feast, and they ate and drank. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'In the morning they rose early and exchanged oaths. And Isaac sent
        them on their way, and they departed from him in peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "That same day Isaac\u2019s servants came and told him about the well
        that they had dug and said to him, \u201CWe have found water.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'He called it Shibah;[[COMMENT(0)]] therefore the name of the city
        is Beersheba to this day.  '
      comments:
      - number: '26:33 '
        content: 'sounds like the Hebrew for '
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'When Esau was forty years old, he took Judith the daughter of Beeri
        the Hittite to be his wife, and Basemath the daughter of Elon the Hittite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: and they made life bitter[[COMMENT(0)]] for Isaac and Rebekah.
      comments:
      - number: '26:35 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Isaac Blesses Jacob'
      title: Isaac Blesses Jacob
      number: 1
      content: "  When Isaac was old and his eyes were dim so that he could not see,
        he called Esau his older son and said to him, \u201CMy son\u201D; and he
        answered, \u201CHere I am.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He said, \u201CBehold, I am old; I do not know the day of my death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now then, take your weapons, your quiver and your bow, and go out
        to the field and hunt game for me, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "and prepare for me delicious food, such as I love, and bring it to
        me so that I may eat, that my soul may bless you before I die.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now Rebekah was listening when Isaac spoke to his son Esau. So when
        Esau went to the field to hunt for game and bring it, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Rebekah said to her son Jacob, \u201CI heard your father speak to
        your brother Esau, "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u2018Bring me game and prepare for me delicious food, that I may
        eat it and bless you before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> before I die.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now therefore, my son, obey my voice as I command you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Go to the flock and bring me two good young goats, so that I may
        prepare from them delicious food for your father, such as he loves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And you shall bring it to your father to eat, so that he may bless
        you before he dies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But Jacob said to Rebekah his mother, \u201CBehold, my brother Esau
        is a hairy man, and I am a smooth man. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Perhaps my father will feel me, and I shall seem to be mocking him
        and bring a curse upon myself and not a blessing.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "His mother said to him, \u201CLet your curse be on me, my son; only
        obey my voice, and go, bring them to me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So he went and took them and brought them to his mother, and his
        mother prepared delicious food, such as his father loved. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then Rebekah took the best garments of Esau her older son, which
        were with her in the house, and put them on Jacob her younger son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And the skins of the young goats she put on his hands and on the
        smooth part of his neck. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And she put the delicious food and the bread, which she had prepared,
        into the hand of her son Jacob.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So he went in to his father and said, \u201CMy father.\u201D And
        he said, \u201CHere I am. Who are you, my son?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Jacob said to his father, \u201CI am Esau your firstborn. I have
        done as you told me; now sit up and eat of my game, that your soul may bless
        me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But Isaac said to his son, \u201CHow is it that you have found it
        so quickly, my son?\u201D He answered, \u201CBecause the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God granted me success.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Isaac said to Jacob, \u201CPlease come near, that I may feel
        you, my son, to know whether you are really my son Esau or not.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So Jacob went near to Isaac his father, who felt him and said, \u201CThe
        voice is Jacob\u2019s voice, but the hands are the hands of Esau.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And he did not recognize him, because his hands were hairy like his
        brother Esau\u2019s hands. So he blessed him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "He said, \u201CAre you really my son Esau?\u201D He answered, \u201CI
        am.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then he said, \u201CBring it near to me, that I may eat of my son\u2019s
        game and bless you.\u201D So he brought it near to him, and he ate; and he
        brought him wine, and he drank.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then his father Isaac said to him, \u201CCome near and kiss me, my
        son.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "So he came near and kissed him. And Isaac smelled the smell of his
        garments and blessed him and said,\u201CSee, the smell of my sonis as the
        smell of a field that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has blessed!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'May God give you of the dew of heavenand of the fatness of the earthand
        plenty of grain and wine.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Let peoples serve you,and nations bow down to you.  Be lord over
        your brothers,and may your mother\u2019s sons bow down to you.  Cursed be
        everyone who curses you,and blessed be everyone who blesses you!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'As soon as Isaac had finished blessing Jacob, when Jacob had scarcely
        gone out from the presence of Isaac his father, Esau his brother came in
        from his hunting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "He also prepared delicious food and brought it to his father. And
        he said to his father, \u201CLet my father arise and eat of his son\u2019s
        game, that you may bless me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "His father Isaac said to him, \u201CWho are you?\u201D He answered,
        \u201CI am your son, your firstborn, Esau.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then Isaac trembled very violently and said, \u201CWho was it then
        that hunted game and brought it to me, and I ate it all before you came,
        and I have blessed him? Yes, and he shall be blessed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "As soon as Esau heard the words of his father, he cried out with
        an exceedingly great and bitter cry and said to his father, \u201CBless me,
        even me also, O my father!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "But he said, \u201CYour brother came deceitfully, and he has taken
        away your blessing.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Esau said, \u201CIs he not rightly named Jacob?[[COMMENT(0)]] For
        he has cheated me these two times. He took away my birthright, and behold,
        now he has taken away my blessing.\u201D Then he said, \u201CHave you not
        reserved a blessing for me?\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '27:36 '
        content: 'means , or '
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Isaac answered and said to Esau, \u201CBehold, I have made him lord
        over you, and all his brothers I have given to him for servants, and with
        grain and wine I have sustained him. What then can I do for you, my son?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Esau said to his father, \u201CHave you but one blessing, my father?
        Bless me, even me also, O my father.\u201D And Esau lifted up his voice and
        wept.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Then Isaac his father answered and said to him:\u201CBehold, away
        from[[COMMENT(0)]] the fatness of the earth shall your dwelling be,and away
        from the dew of heaven on high.  "
      comments:
      - number: '27:39 '
        content: 'Or Or '
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "By your sword you shall live,and you shall serve your brother;but
        when you grow restless  you shall break his yoke from your neck.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Now Esau hated Jacob because of the blessing with which his father
        had blessed him, and Esau said to himself, \u201CThe days of mourning for
        my father are approaching; then I will kill my brother Jacob.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "But the words of Esau her older son were told to Rebekah. So she
        sent and called Jacob her younger son and said to him, \u201CBehold, your
        brother Esau comforts himself about you by planning to kill you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Now therefore, my son, obey my voice. Arise, flee to Laban my brother
        in Haran '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "and stay with him a while, until your brother\u2019s fury turns away\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "until your brother\u2019s anger turns away from you, and he forgets
        what you have done to him. Then I will send and bring you from there. Why
        should I be bereft of you both in one day?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "Then Rebekah said to Isaac, \u201CI loathe my life because of the
        Hittite women.[[COMMENT(0)]]  If Jacob marries one of the Hittite women like
        these, one of the women of the land, what good will my life be to me?\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '27:46 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jacob Sent to Laban'
      title: Jacob Sent to Laban
      number: 1
      content: "  Then Isaac called Jacob and blessed him and directed him, \u201CYou
        must not take a wife from the Canaanite women. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Arise, go to Paddan-aram to the house of Bethuel your mother\u2019s
        father, and take as your wife from there one of the daughters of Laban your
        mother\u2019s brother. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'God Almighty[[COMMENT(0)]] bless you and make you fruitful and multiply
        you, that you may become a company of peoples. '
      comments:
      - number: '28:3 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "May he give the blessing of Abraham to you and to your offspring
        with you, that you may take possession of the land of your sojournings that
        God gave to Abraham!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Esau Marries an Ishmaelite'
      title: Esau Marries an Ishmaelite
      number: 5
      content: "Thus Isaac sent Jacob away. And he went to Paddan-aram, to Laban,
        the son of Bethuel the Aramean, the brother of Rebekah, Jacob\u2019s and
        Esau\u2019s mother.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Now Esau saw that Isaac had blessed Jacob and sent him away to Paddan-aram
        to take a wife from there, and that as he blessed him he directed him, \u201CYou
        must not take a wife from the Canaanite women,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and that Jacob had obeyed his father and his mother and gone to Paddan-aram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So when Esau saw that the Canaanite women did not please Isaac his
        father, '
      comments: []
    - name: "9: Jacob\u2019s Dream"
      title: "Jacob\u2019s Dream"
      number: 9
      content: "Esau went to Ishmael and took as his wife, besides the wives he had,
        Mahalath the daughter of Ishmael, Abraham\u2019s son, the sister of Nebaioth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Jacob left Beersheba and went toward Haran. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And he came to a certain place and stayed there that night, because
        the sun had set. Taking one of the stones of the place, he put it under his
        head and lay down in that place to sleep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And he dreamed, and behold, there was a ladder[[COMMENT(0)]] set
        up on the earth, and the top of it reached to heaven. And behold, the angels
        of God were ascending and descending on it! '
      comments:
      - number: '28:12 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And behold, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> stood above it[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and said, \u201CI am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Abraham
        your father and the God of Isaac. The land on which you lie I will give to
        you and to your offspring. "
      comments:
      - number: '28:13 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Your offspring shall be like the dust of the earth, and you shall
        spread abroad to the west and to the east and to the north and to the south,
        and in you and your offspring shall all the families of the earth be blessed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Behold, I am with you and will keep you wherever you go, and will
        bring you back to this land. For I will not leave you until I have done what
        I have promised you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Jacob awoke from his sleep and said, \u201CSurely the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is in this place, and I did not know it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And he was afraid and said, \u201CHow awesome is this place! This
        is none other than the house of God, and this is the gate of heaven.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So early in the morning Jacob took the stone that he had put under
        his head and set it up for a pillar and poured oil on the top of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He called the name of that place Bethel,[[COMMENT(0)]] but the name
        of the city was Luz at the first. '
      comments:
      - number: '28:19 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Jacob made a vow, saying, \u201CIf God will be with me and will
        keep me in this way that I go, and will give me bread to eat and clothing
        to wear, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "so that I come again to my father\u2019s house in peace, then the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> shall be my God, "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "and this stone, which I have set up for a pillar, shall be God\u2019s
        house. And of all that you give me I will give a full tenth to you.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jacob Marries Leah and Rachel'
      title: Jacob Marries Leah and Rachel
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Jacob went on his journey and came to the land of the people
        of the east. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "As he looked, he saw a well in the field, and behold, three flocks
        of sheep lying beside it, for out of that well the flocks were watered. The
        stone on the well\u2019s mouth was large, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and when all the flocks were gathered there, the shepherds would
        roll the stone from the mouth of the well and water the sheep, and put the
        stone back in its place over the mouth of the well.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Jacob said to them, \u201CMy brothers, where do you come from?\u201D
        They said, \u201CWe are from Haran.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "He said to them, \u201CDo you know Laban the son of Nahor?\u201D
        They said, \u201CWe know him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "He said to them, \u201CIs it well with him?\u201D They said, \u201CIt
        is well; and see, Rachel his daughter is coming with the sheep!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "He said, \u201CBehold, it is still high day; it is not time for the
        livestock to be gathered together. Water the sheep and go, pasture them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But they said, \u201CWe cannot until all the flocks are gathered
        together and the stone is rolled from the mouth of the well; then we water
        the sheep.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "While he was still speaking with them, Rachel came with her father\u2019s
        sheep, for she was a shepherdess. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Now as soon as Jacob saw Rachel the daughter of Laban his mother\u2019s
        brother, and the sheep of Laban his mother\u2019s brother, Jacob came near
        and rolled the stone from the well\u2019s mouth and watered the flock of
        Laban his mother\u2019s brother. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then Jacob kissed Rachel and wept aloud. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Jacob told Rachel that he was her father\u2019s kinsman, and
        that he was Rebekah\u2019s son, and she ran and told her father.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "As soon as Laban heard the news about Jacob, his sister\u2019s son,
        he ran to meet him and embraced him and kissed him and brought him to his
        house. Jacob told Laban all these things, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "and Laban said to him, \u201CSurely you are my bone and my flesh!\u201D
        And he stayed with him a month.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Laban said to Jacob, \u201CBecause you are my kinsman, should
        you therefore serve me for nothing? Tell me, what shall your wages be?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now Laban had two daughters. The name of the older was Leah, and
        the name of the younger was Rachel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Leah\u2019s eyes were weak,[[COMMENT(0)]] but Rachel was beautiful
        in form and appearance. "
      comments:
      - number: '29:17 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Jacob loved Rachel. And he said, \u201CI will serve you seven years
        for your younger daughter Rachel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Laban said, \u201CIt is better that I give her to you than that I
        should give her to any other man; stay with me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So Jacob served seven years for Rachel, and they seemed to him but
        a few days because of the love he had for her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Jacob said to Laban, \u201CGive me my wife that I may go in
        to her, for my time is completed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So Laban gathered together all the people of the place and made a
        feast. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But in the evening he took his daughter Leah and brought her to Jacob,
        and he went in to her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '(Laban gave[[COMMENT(0)]]  his female servant Zilpah to his daughter
        Leah to be her servant.) '
      comments:
      - number: '29:24 '
        content: Or ; also verse 29
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And in the morning, behold, it was Leah! And Jacob said to Laban,
        \u201CWhat is this you have done to me? Did I not serve with you for Rachel?
        Why then have you deceived me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Laban said, \u201CIt is not so done in our country, to give the younger
        before the firstborn. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Complete the week of this one, and we will give you the other also
        in return for serving me another seven years.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Jacob did so, and completed her week. Then Laban gave him his daughter
        Rachel to be his wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '(Laban gave his female servant Bilhah to his daughter Rachel to be
        her servant.) '
      comments: []
    - name: "30: Jacob\u2019s Children"
      title: "Jacob\u2019s Children"
      number: 30
      content: 'So Jacob went in to Rachel also, and he loved Rachel more than Leah,
        and served Laban for another seven years.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'When the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> saw that Leah was hated, he
        opened her womb, but Rachel was barren. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And Leah conceived and bore a son, and she called his name Reuben,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        for she said, \u201CBecause the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  has looked upon
        my affliction; for now my husband will love me.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '29:32 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "She conceived again and bore a son, and said, \u201CBecause the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has heard that I am hated, he has given me this son also.\u201D And she called
        his name Simeon.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '29:33 '
        content: 'sounds like the Hebrew for '
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Again she conceived and bore a son, and said, \u201CNow this time
        my husband will be attached to me, because I have borne him three sons.\u201D
        Therefore his name was called Levi.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '29:34 '
        content: 'sounds like the Hebrew for '
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And she conceived again and bore a son, and said, \u201CThis time
        I will praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D Therefore she called
        his name Judah.[[COMMENT(0)]] Then she ceased bearing."
      comments:
      - number: '29:35 '
        content: 'sounds like the Hebrew for '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "  When Rachel saw that she bore Jacob no children, she envied her
        sister. She said to Jacob, \u201CGive me children, or I shall die!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Jacob\u2019s anger was kindled against Rachel, and he said, \u201CAm
        I in the place of God, who has withheld from you the fruit of the womb?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then she said, \u201CHere is my servant Bilhah; go in to her, so
        that she may give birth on my behalf,[[COMMENT(0)]] that even I may have
        children through her.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '30:3 '
        content: 'Hebrew Hebrew , which sounds like the Hebrew for '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So she gave him her servant Bilhah as a wife, and Jacob went in to
        her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Bilhah conceived and bore Jacob a son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Rachel said, \u201CGod has judged me, and has also heard my
        voice and given me a son.\u201D Therefore she called his name Dan.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '30:6 '
        content: 'sounds like the Hebrew for '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Rachel\u2019s servant Bilhah conceived again and bore Jacob a second
        son. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Rachel said, \u201CWith mighty wrestlings[[COMMENT(0)]] I have
        wrestled with my sister and have prevailed.\u201D So she called his name
        Naphtali.  "
      comments:
      - number: '30:8 '
        content: 'Hebrew sounds like the Hebrew for '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When Leah saw that she had ceased bearing children, she took her
        servant Zilpah and gave her to Jacob as a wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Leah\u2019s servant Zilpah bore Jacob a son. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And Leah said, \u201CGood fortune has come!\u201D so she called his
        name Gad.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '30:11 '
        content: 'sounds like the Hebrew for '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Leah\u2019s servant Zilpah bore Jacob a second son. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Leah said, \u201CHappy am I! For women have called me happy.\u201D
        So she called his name Asher.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '30:13 '
        content: 'sounds like the Hebrew for '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "In the days of wheat harvest Reuben went and found mandrakes in the
        field and brought them to his mother Leah. Then Rachel said to Leah, \u201CPlease
        give me some of your son\u2019s mandrakes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But she said to her, \u201CIs it a small matter that you have taken
        away my husband? Would you take away my son\u2019s mandrakes also?\u201D
        Rachel said, \u201CThen he may lie with you tonight in exchange for your
        son\u2019s mandrakes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When Jacob came from the field in the evening, Leah went out to meet
        him and said, \u201CYou must come in to me, for I have hired you with my
        son\u2019s mandrakes.\u201D So he lay with her that night. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And God listened to Leah, and she conceived and bore Jacob a fifth
        son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Leah said, \u201CGod has given me my wages because I gave my servant
        to my husband.\u201D So she called his name Issachar.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '30:18 '
        content: 'sounds like the Hebrew for , or '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And Leah conceived again, and she bore Jacob a sixth son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Leah said, \u201CGod has endowed me with a good endowment; now
        my husband will honor me, because I have borne him six sons.\u201D So she
        called his name Zebulun.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '30:20 '
        content: 'sounds like the Hebrew for '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Afterward she bore a daughter and called her name Dinah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then God remembered Rachel, and God listened to her and opened her
        womb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "She conceived and bore a son and said, \u201CGod has taken away my
        reproach.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "24: Jacob\u2019s Prosperity"
      title: "Jacob\u2019s Prosperity"
      number: 24
      content: "And she called his name Joseph,[[COMMENT(0)]] saying, \u201CMay the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> add to me another son!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '30:24 '
        content: 'means , and sounds like the Hebrew for '
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "As soon as Rachel had borne Joseph, Jacob said to Laban, \u201CSend
        me away, that I may go to my own home and country. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Give me my wives and my children for whom I have served you, that
        I may go, for you know the service that I have given you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But Laban said to him, \u201CIf I have found favor in your sight,
        I have learned by divination that[[COMMENT(0)]] the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has blessed me because of you. "
      comments:
      - number: '30:27 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Name your wages, and I will give it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Jacob said to him, \u201CYou yourself know how I have served you,
        and how your livestock has fared with me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "For you had little before I came, and it has increased abundantly,
        and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has blessed you wherever I turned. But
        now when shall I provide for my own household also?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "He said, \u201CWhat shall I give you?\u201D Jacob said, \u201CYou
        shall not give me anything. If you will do this for me, I will again pasture
        your flock and keep it: "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'let me pass through all your flock today, removing from it every
        speckled and spotted sheep and every black lamb, and the spotted and speckled
        among the goats, and they shall be my wages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "So my honesty will answer for me later, when you come to look into
        my wages with you. Every one that is not speckled and spotted among the goats
        and black among the lambs, if found with me, shall be counted stolen.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Laban said, \u201CGood! Let it be as you have said.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'But that day Laban removed the male goats that were striped and spotted,
        and all the female goats that were speckled and spotted, every one that had
        white on it, and every lamb that was black, and put them in the charge of
        his sons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And he set a distance of three days\u2019 journey between himself
        and Jacob, and Jacob pastured the rest of Laban\u2019s flock.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Then Jacob took fresh sticks of poplar and almond and plane trees,
        and peeled white streaks in them, exposing the white of the sticks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'He set the sticks that he had peeled in front of the flocks in the
        troughs, that is, the watering places, where the flocks came to drink. And
        since they bred when they came to drink, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'the flocks bred in front of the sticks and so the flocks brought
        forth striped, speckled, and spotted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "And Jacob separated the lambs and set the faces of the flocks toward
        the striped and all the black in the flock of Laban. He put his own droves
        apart and did not put them with Laban\u2019s flock. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Whenever the stronger of the flock were breeding, Jacob would lay
        the sticks in the troughs before the eyes of the flock, that they might breed
        among the sticks, '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "but for the feebler of the flock he would not lay them there. So
        the feebler would be Laban\u2019s, and the stronger Jacob\u2019s. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: Thus the man increased greatly and had large flocks, female servants
        and male servants, and camels and donkeys.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jacob Flees from Laban'
      title: Jacob Flees from Laban
      number: 1
      content: "  Now Jacob heard that the sons of Laban were saying, \u201CJacob
        has taken all that was our father\u2019s, and from what was our father\u2019s
        he has gained all this wealth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Jacob saw that Laban did not regard him with favor as before. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Jacob, \u201CReturn
        to the land of your fathers and to your kindred, and I will be with you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So Jacob sent and called Rachel and Leah into the field where his
        flock was '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and said to them, \u201CI see that your father does not regard me
        with favor as he did before. But the God of my father has been with me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You know that I have served your father with all my strength, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'yet your father has cheated me and changed my wages ten times. But
        God did not permit him to harm me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "If he said, \u2018The spotted shall be your wages,\u2019 then all
        the flock bore spotted; and if he said, \u2018The striped shall be your wages,\u2019
        then all the flock bore striped. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Thus God has taken away the livestock of your father and given them
        to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'In the breeding season of the flock I lifted up my eyes and saw in
        a dream that the goats that mated with the flock were striped, spotted, and
        mottled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then the angel of God said to me in the dream, \u2018Jacob,\u2019
        and I said, \u2018Here I am!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And he said, \u2018Lift up your eyes and see, all the goats that
        mate with the flock are striped, spotted, and mottled, for I have seen all
        that Laban is doing to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "I am the God of Bethel, where you anointed a pillar and made a vow
        to me. Now arise, go out from this land and return to the land of your kindred.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Rachel and Leah answered and said to him, \u201CIs there any
        portion or inheritance left to us in our father\u2019s house? "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Are we not regarded by him as foreigners? For he has sold us, and
        he has indeed devoured our money. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "All the wealth that God has taken away from our father belongs to
        us and to our children. Now then, whatever God has said to you, do.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So Jacob arose and set his sons and his wives on camels. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He drove away all his livestock, all his property that he had gained,
        the livestock in his possession that he had acquired in Paddan-aram, to go
        to the land of Canaan to his father Isaac. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Laban had gone to shear his sheep, and Rachel stole her father\u2019s
        household gods. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Jacob tricked[[COMMENT(0)]] Laban the Aramean, by not telling
        him that he intended to flee. '
      comments:
      - number: '31:20 '
        content: Hebrew ; also verses 26, 27
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He fled with all that he had and arose and crossed the Euphrates,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and set his face toward the hill country of Gilead.  '
      comments:
      - number: '31:21 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'When it was told Laban on the third day that Jacob had fled, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'he took his kinsmen with him and pursued him for seven days and followed
        close after him into the hill country of Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "But God came to Laban the Aramean in a dream by night and said to
        him, \u201CBe careful not to say anything to Jacob, either good or bad.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And Laban overtook Jacob. Now Jacob had pitched his tent in the hill
        country, and Laban with his kinsmen pitched tents in the hill country of
        Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And Laban said to Jacob, \u201CWhat have you done, that you have
        tricked me and driven away my daughters like captives of the sword? "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Why did you flee secretly and trick me, and did not tell me, so that
        I might have sent you away with mirth and songs, with tambourine and lyre? '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And why did you not permit me to kiss my sons and my daughters farewell?
        Now you have done foolishly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "It is in my power to do you harm. But the God of your[[COMMENT(0)]]
        father spoke to me last night, saying, \u2018Be careful not to say anything
        to Jacob, either good or bad.\u2019 "
      comments:
      - number: '31:29 '
        content: The Hebrew for is plural here
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And now you have gone away because you longed greatly for your father\u2019s
        house, but why did you steal my gods?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Jacob answered and said to Laban, \u201CBecause I was afraid, for
        I thought that you would take your daughters from me by force. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Anyone with whom you find your gods shall not live. In the presence
        of our kinsmen point out what I have that is yours, and take it.\u201D Now
        Jacob did not know that Rachel had stolen them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "So Laban went into Jacob\u2019s tent and into Leah\u2019s tent and
        into the tent of the two female servants, but he did not find them. And he
        went out of Leah\u2019s tent and entered Rachel\u2019s. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Now Rachel had taken the household gods and put them in the camel\u2019s
        saddle and sat on them. Laban felt all about the tent, but did not find them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And she said to her father, \u201CLet not my lord be angry that I
        cannot rise before you, for the way of women is upon me.\u201D So he searched
        but did not find the household gods.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Then Jacob became angry and berated Laban. Jacob said to Laban, \u201CWhat
        is my offense? What is my sin, that you have hotly pursued me? "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'For you have felt through all my goods; what have you found of all
        your household goods? Set it here before my kinsmen and your kinsmen, that
        they may decide between us two. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'These twenty years I have been with you. Your ewes and your female
        goats have not miscarried, and I have not eaten the rams of your flocks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'What was torn by wild beasts I did not bring to you. I bore the loss
        of it myself. From my hand you required it, whether stolen by day or stolen
        by night. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'There I was: by day the heat consumed me, and the cold by night,
        and my sleep fled from my eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'These twenty years I have been in your house. I served you fourteen
        years for your two daughters, and six years for your flock, and you have
        changed my wages ten times. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "If the God of my father, the God of Abraham and the Fear of Isaac,
        had not been on my side, surely now you would have sent me away empty-handed.
        God saw my affliction and the labor of my hands and rebuked you last night.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Then Laban answered and said to Jacob, \u201CThe daughters are my
        daughters, the children are my children, the flocks are my flocks, and all
        that you see is mine. But what can I do this day for these my daughters or
        for their children whom they have borne? "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "Come now, let us make a covenant, you and I. And let it be a witness
        between you and me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'So Jacob took a stone and set it up as a pillar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "And Jacob said to his kinsmen, \u201CGather stones.\u201D And they
        took stones and made a heap, and they ate there by the heap. "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'Laban called it Jegar-sahadutha,[[COMMENT(0)]] but Jacob called it
        Galeed.  '
      comments:
      - number: '31:47 '
        content: 'Aramaic Hebrew '
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "Laban said, \u201CThis heap is a witness between you and me today.\u201D
        Therefore he named it Galeed, "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "and Mizpah,[[COMMENT(0)]] for he said, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        watch between you and me, when we are out of one another\u2019s sight. "
      comments:
      - number: '31:49 '
        content: 'means   '
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "If you oppress my daughters, or if you take wives besides my daughters,
        although no one is with us, see, God is witness between you and me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "Then Laban said to Jacob, \u201CSee this heap and the pillar, which
        I have set between you and me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'This heap is a witness, and the pillar is a witness, that I will
        not pass over this heap to you, and you will not pass over this heap and
        this pillar to me, to do harm. '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "The God of Abraham and the God of Nahor, the God of their father,
        judge between us.\u201D So Jacob swore by the Fear of his father Isaac, "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'and Jacob offered a sacrifice in the hill country and called his
        kinsmen to eat bread. They ate bread and spent the night in the hill country.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: '  [[COMMENT(0)]] Early in the morning Laban arose and kissed his
        grandchildren and his daughters and blessed them. Then Laban departed and
        returned home.'
      comments:
      - number: '31:55 '
        content: '  Ch 32:1 in Hebrew  '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jacob Fears Esau'
      title: Jacob Fears Esau
      number: 1
      content: '  Jacob went on his way, and the angels of God met him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And when Jacob saw them he said, \u201CThis is God\u2019s camp!\u201D
        So he called the name of that place Mahanaim.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '32:2 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Jacob sent[[COMMENT(0)]] messengers before him to Esau his brother
        in the land of Seir, the country of Edom, '
      comments:
      - number: '32:3 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "instructing them, \u201CThus you shall say to my lord Esau: Thus
        says your servant Jacob, \u2018I have sojourned with Laban and stayed until
        now. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "I have oxen, donkeys, flocks, male servants, and female servants.
        I have sent to tell my lord, in order that I may find favor in your sight.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the messengers returned to Jacob, saying, \u201CWe came to your
        brother Esau, and he is coming to meet you, and there are four hundred men
        with him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then Jacob was greatly afraid and distressed. He divided the people
        who were with him, and the flocks and herds and camels, into two camps, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "thinking, \u201CIf Esau comes to the one camp and attacks it, then
        the camp that is left will escape.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Jacob said, \u201CO God of my father Abraham and God of my father
        Isaac, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who said to me, \u2018Return to your
        country and to your kindred, that I may do you good,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I am not worthy of the least of all the deeds of steadfast love and
        all the faithfulness that you have shown to your servant, for with only my
        staff I crossed this Jordan, and now I have become two camps. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Please deliver me from the hand of my brother, from the hand of Esau,
        for I fear him, that he may come and attack me, the mothers with the children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But you said, \u2018I will surely do you good, and make your offspring
        as the sand of the sea, which cannot be numbered for multitude.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So he stayed there that night, and from what he had with him he took
        a present for his brother Esau, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'two hundred female goats and twenty male goats, two hundred ewes
        and twenty rams, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'thirty milking camels and their calves, forty cows and ten bulls,
        twenty female donkeys and ten male donkeys. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "These he handed over to his servants, every drove by itself, and
        said to his servants, \u201CPass on ahead of me and put a space between drove
        and drove.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "He instructed the first, \u201CWhen Esau my brother meets you and
        asks you, \u2018To whom do you belong? Where are you going? And whose are
        these ahead of you?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "then you shall say, \u2018They belong to your servant Jacob. They
        are a present sent to my lord Esau. And moreover, he is behind us.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "He likewise instructed the second and the third and all who followed
        the droves, \u201CYou shall say the same thing to Esau when you find him, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "and you shall say, \u2018Moreover, your servant Jacob is behind us.\u2019\u201D
        For he thought, \u201CI may appease him[[COMMENT(0)]] with the present that
        goes ahead of me, and afterward I shall see his face. Perhaps he will accept
        me.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '32:20 '
        content: 'Hebrew Hebrew '
    - name: '21: Jacob Wrestles with God'
      title: Jacob Wrestles with God
      number: 21
      content: 'So the present passed on ahead of him, and he himself stayed that
        night in the camp.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The same night he arose and took his two wives, his two female servants,
        and his eleven children,[[COMMENT(0)]] and crossed the ford of the Jabbok. '
      comments:
      - number: '32:22 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'He took them and sent them across the stream, and everything else
        that he had. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And Jacob was left alone. And a man wrestled with him until the breaking
        of the day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "When the man saw that he did not prevail against Jacob, he touched
        his hip socket, and Jacob\u2019s hip was put out of joint as he wrestled
        with him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then he said, \u201CLet me go, for the day has broken.\u201D But
        Jacob said, \u201CI will not let you go unless you bless me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And he said to him, \u201CWhat is your name?\u201D And he said, \u201CJacob.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then he said, \u201CYour name shall no longer be called Jacob, but
        Israel,[[COMMENT(0)]] for you have striven with God and with men, and have
        prevailed.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '32:28 '
        content: 'means , or '
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then Jacob asked him, \u201CPlease tell me your name.\u201D But he
        said, \u201CWhy is it that you ask my name?\u201D And there he blessed him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "So Jacob called the name of the place Peniel,[[COMMENT(0)]] saying,
        \u201CFor I have seen God face to face, and yet my life has been delivered.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '32:30 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The sun rose upon him as he passed Penuel, limping because of his
        hip. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Therefore to this day the people of Israel do not eat the sinew of
        the thigh that is on the hip socket, because he touched the socket of Jacob\u2019s
        hip on the sinew of the thigh."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jacob Meets Esau'
      title: Jacob Meets Esau
      number: 1
      content: '  And Jacob lifted up his eyes and looked, and behold, Esau was coming,
        and four hundred men with him. So he divided the children among Leah and
        Rachel and the two female servants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he put the servants with their children in front, then Leah with
        her children, and Rachel and Joseph last of all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He himself went on before them, bowing himself to the ground seven
        times, until he came near to his brother.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  But Esau ran to meet him and embraced him and fell on his neck
        and kissed him, and they wept. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And when Esau lifted up his eyes and saw the women and children,
        he said, \u201CWho are these with you?\u201D Jacob said, \u201CThe children
        whom God has graciously given your servant.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the servants drew near, they and their children, and bowed down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Leah likewise and her children drew near and bowed down. And last
        Joseph and Rachel drew near, and they bowed down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Esau said, \u201CWhat do you mean by all this company[[COMMENT(0)]]
        that I met?\u201D Jacob answered, \u201CTo find favor in the sight of my
        lord.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '33:8 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But Esau said, \u201CI have enough, my brother; keep what you have
        for yourself.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Jacob said, \u201CNo, please, if I have found favor in your sight,
        then accept my present from my hand. For I have seen your face, which is
        like seeing the face of God, and you have accepted me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Please accept my blessing that is brought to you, because God has
        dealt graciously with me, and because I have enough.\u201D Thus he urged
        him, and he took it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Esau said, \u201CLet us journey on our way, and I will go ahead
        of[[COMMENT(0)]] you.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '33:12 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But Jacob said to him, \u201CMy lord knows that the children are
        frail, and that the nursing flocks and herds are a care to me. If they are
        driven hard for one day, all the flocks will die. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Let my lord pass on ahead of his servant, and I will lead on slowly,
        at the pace of the livestock that are ahead of me and at the pace of the
        children, until I come to my lord in Seir.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So Esau said, \u201CLet me leave with you some of the people who
        are with me.\u201D But he said, \u201CWhat need is there? Let me find favor
        in the sight of my lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So Esau returned that day on his way to Seir. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But Jacob journeyed to Succoth, and built himself a house and made
        booths for his livestock. Therefore the name of the place is called Succoth.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '33:17 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And Jacob came safely[[COMMENT(0)]] to the city of Shechem, which
        is in the land of Canaan, on his way from Paddan-aram, and he camped before
        the city. '
      comments:
      - number: '33:18 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And from the sons of Hamor, Shechem\u2019s father, he bought for
        a hundred pieces of money[[COMMENT(0)]] the piece of land on which he had
        pitched his tent. "
      comments:
      - number: '33:19 '
        content: Hebrew ; a unit of money of unknown value
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: There he erected an altar and called it El-Elohe-Israel.[[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: '33:20 '
        content: 'means '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Defiling of Dinah'
      title: The Defiling of Dinah
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Dinah the daughter of Leah, whom she had borne to Jacob, went
        out to see the women of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And when Shechem the son of Hamor the Hivite, the prince of the land,
        saw her, he seized her and lay with her and humiliated her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And his soul was drawn to Dinah the daughter of Jacob. He loved the
        young woman and spoke tenderly to her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So Shechem spoke to his father Hamor, saying, \u201CGet me this girl
        for my wife.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now Jacob heard that he had defiled his daughter Dinah. But his sons
        were with his livestock in the field, so Jacob held his peace until they
        came. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Hamor the father of Shechem went out to Jacob to speak with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The sons of Jacob had come in from the field as soon as they heard
        of it, and the men were indignant and very angry, because he had done an
        outrageous thing in Israel by lying with Jacob\u2019s daughter, for such
        a thing must not be done.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But Hamor spoke with them, saying, \u201CThe soul of my son Shechem
        longs for your[[COMMENT(0)]] daughter. Please give her to him to be his wife. "
      comments:
      - number: '34:8 '
        content: The Hebrew for is plural here
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Make marriages with us. Give your daughters to us, and take our daughters
        for yourselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "You shall dwell with us, and the land shall be open to you. Dwell
        and trade in it, and get property in it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Shechem also said to her father and to her brothers, \u201CLet me
        find favor in your eyes, and whatever you say to me I will give. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Ask me for as great a bride-price[[COMMENT(0)]] and gift as you will,
        and I will give whatever you say to me. Only give me the young woman to be
        my wife.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '34:12 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The sons of Jacob answered Shechem and his father Hamor deceitfully,
        because he had defiled their sister Dinah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "They said to them, \u201CWe cannot do this thing, to give our sister
        to one who is uncircumcised, for that would be a disgrace to us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Only on this condition will we agree with you\u2014that you will
        become as we are by every male among you being circumcised. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then we will give our daughters to you, and we will take your daughters
        to ourselves, and we will dwell with you and become one people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But if you will not listen to us and be circumcised, then we will
        take our daughter, and we will be gone.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Their words pleased Hamor and Hamor\u2019s son Shechem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And the young man did not delay to do the thing, because he delighted
        in Jacob\u2019s daughter. Now he was the most honored of all his father\u2019s
        house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So Hamor and his son Shechem came to the gate of their city and spoke
        to the men of their city, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CThese men are at peace with us; let them dwell in the land
        and trade in it, for behold, the land is large enough for them. Let us take
        their daughters as wives, and let us give them our daughters. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Only on this condition will the men agree to dwell with us to become
        one people\u2014when every male among us is circumcised as they are circumcised. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Will not their livestock, their property and all their beasts be
        ours? Only let us agree with them, and they will dwell with us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And all who went out of the gate of his city listened to Hamor and
        his son Shechem, and every male was circumcised, all who went out of the
        gate of his city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "On the third day, when they were sore, two of the sons of Jacob,
        Simeon and Levi, Dinah\u2019s brothers, took their swords and came against
        the city while it felt secure and killed all the males. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "They killed Hamor and his son Shechem with the sword and took Dinah
        out of Shechem\u2019s house and went away. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The sons of Jacob came upon the slain and plundered the city, because
        they had defiled their sister. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'They took their flocks and their herds, their donkeys, and whatever
        was in the city and in the field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'All their wealth, all their little ones and their wives, all that
        was in the houses, they captured and plundered.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then Jacob said to Simeon and Levi, \u201CYou have brought trouble
        on me by making me stink to the inhabitants of the land, the Canaanites and
        the Perizzites. My numbers are few, and if they gather themselves against
        me and attack me, I shall be destroyed, both I and my household.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "But they said, \u201CShould he treat our sister like a prostitute?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Blesses and Renames Jacob'
      title: God Blesses and Renames Jacob
      number: 1
      content: "  God said to Jacob, \u201CArise, go up to Bethel and dwell there.
        Make an altar there to the God who appeared to you when you fled from your
        brother Esau.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So Jacob said to his household and to all who were with him, \u201CPut
        away the foreign gods that are among you and purify yourselves and change
        your garments. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then let us arise and go up to Bethel, so that I may make there an
        altar to the God who answers me in the day of my distress and has been with
        me wherever I have gone.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So they gave to Jacob all the foreign gods that they had, and the
        rings that were in their ears. Jacob hid them under the terebinth tree that
        was near Shechem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And as they journeyed, a terror from God fell upon the cities that
        were around them, so that they did not pursue the sons of Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Jacob came to Luz (that is, Bethel), which is in the land of
        Canaan, he and all the people who were with him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and there he built an altar and called the place El-bethel,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        because there God had revealed himself to him when he fled from his brother. '
      comments:
      - number: '35:7 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Deborah, Rebekah\u2019s nurse, died, and she was buried under
        an oak below Bethel. So he called its name Allon-bacuth.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '35:8 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'God appeared[[COMMENT(0)]] to Jacob again, when he came from Paddan-aram,
        and blessed him. '
      comments:
      - number: '35:9 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And God said to him, \u201CYour name is Jacob; no longer shall your
        name be called Jacob, but Israel shall be your name.\u201D So he called his
        name Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And God said to him, \u201CI am God Almighty:[[COMMENT(0)]] be fruitful
        and multiply. A nation and a company of nations shall come from you, and
        kings shall come from your own body.  "
      comments:
      - number: '35:11 '
        content: 'Hebrew Hebrew '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The land that I gave to Abraham and Isaac I will give to you, and
        I will give the land to your offspring after you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then God went up from him in the place where he had spoken with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Jacob set up a pillar in the place where he had spoken with him,
        a pillar of stone. He poured out a drink offering on it and poured oil on
        it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: The Deaths of Rachel and Isaac'
      title: The Deaths of Rachel and Isaac
      number: 15
      content: 'So Jacob called the name of the place where God had spoken with him
        Bethel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then they journeyed from Bethel. When they were still some distance[[COMMENT(0)]]
        from Ephrath, Rachel went into labor, and she had hard labor. '
      comments:
      - number: '35:16 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And when her labor was at its hardest, the midwife said to her, \u201CDo
        not fear, for you have another son.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And as her soul was departing (for she was dying), she called his
        name Ben-oni;[[COMMENT(0)]]  but his father called him Benjamin.  '
      comments:
      - number: '35:18 '
        content: 'could mean , or means '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So Rachel died, and she was buried on the way to Ephrath (that is,
        Bethlehem), '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "and Jacob set up a pillar over her tomb. It is the pillar of Rachel\u2019s
        tomb, which is there to this day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Israel journeyed on and pitched his tent beyond the tower of Eder.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "While Israel lived in that land, Reuben went and lay with Bilhah
        his father\u2019s concubine. And Israel heard of it.Now the sons of Jacob
        were twelve. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The sons of Leah: Reuben (Jacob\u2019s firstborn), Simeon, Levi,
        Judah, Issachar, and Zebulun. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The sons of Rachel: Joseph and Benjamin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The sons of Bilhah, Rachel\u2019s servant: Dan and Naphtali. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "The sons of Zilpah, Leah\u2019s servant: Gad and Asher. These were
        the sons of Jacob who were born to him in Paddan-aram.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And Jacob came to his father Isaac at Mamre, or Kiriath-arba (that
        is, Hebron), where Abraham and Isaac had sojourned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Now the days of Isaac were 180 years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: And Isaac breathed his last, and he died and was gathered to his people,
        old and full of days. And his sons Esau and Jacob buried him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Esau\u2019s Descendants"
      title: "Esau\u2019s Descendants"
      number: 1
      content: '  These are the generations of Esau (that is, Edom). '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Esau took his wives from the Canaanites: Adah the daughter of Elon
        the Hittite, Oholibamah the daughter of Anah the daughter[[COMMENT(0)]] of
        Zibeon the Hivite, '
      comments:
      - number: '36:2 '
        content: Hebrew; Samaritan, Septuagint, Syriac ; also verse 14
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and Basemath, Ishmael\u2019s daughter, the sister of Nebaioth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And Adah bore to Esau, Eliphaz; Basemath bore Reuel; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and Oholibamah bore Jeush, Jalam, and Korah. These are the sons of
        Esau who were born to him in the land of Canaan.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then Esau took his wives, his sons, his daughters, and all the members
        of his household, his livestock, all his beasts, and all his property that
        he had acquired in the land of Canaan. He went into a land away from his
        brother Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For their possessions were too great for them to dwell together.
        The land of their sojournings could not support them because of their livestock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So Esau settled in the hill country of Seir. (Esau is Edom.)  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'These are the generations of Esau the father of the Edomites in the
        hill country of Seir. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "These are the names of Esau\u2019s sons: Eliphaz the son of Adah
        the wife of Esau, Reuel the son of Basemath the wife of Esau. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The sons of Eliphaz were Teman, Omar, Zepho, Gatam, and Kenaz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "(Timna was a concubine of Eliphaz, Esau\u2019s son; she bore Amalek
        to Eliphaz.) These are the sons of Adah, Esau\u2019s wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "These are the sons of Reuel: Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah.
        These are the sons of Basemath, Esau\u2019s wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "These are the sons of Oholibamah the daughter of Anah the daughter
        of Zibeon, Esau\u2019s wife: she bore to Esau Jeush, Jalam, and Korah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'These are the chiefs of the sons of Esau. The sons of Eliphaz the
        firstborn of Esau: the chiefs Teman, Omar, Zepho, Kenaz, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Korah, Gatam, and Amalek; these are the chiefs of Eliphaz in the
        land of Edom; these are the sons of Adah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "These are the sons of Reuel, Esau\u2019s son: the chiefs Nahath,
        Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah; these are the chiefs of Reuel in the land of
        Edom; these are the sons of Basemath, Esau\u2019s wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "These are the sons of Oholibamah, Esau\u2019s wife: the chiefs Jeush,
        Jalam, and Korah; these are the chiefs born of Oholibamah the daughter of
        Anah, Esau\u2019s wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'These are the sons of Esau (that is, Edom), and these are their chiefs.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  These are the sons of Seir the Horite, the inhabitants of the land:
        Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon, Anah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Dishon, Ezer, and Dishan; these are the chiefs of the Horites, the
        sons of Seir in the land of Edom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "The sons of Lotan were Hori and Hemam; and Lotan\u2019s sister was
        Timna. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'These are the sons of Shobal: Alvan, Manahath, Ebal, Shepho, and
        Onam. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'These are the sons of Zibeon: Aiah and Anah; he is the Anah who found
        the hot springs in the wilderness, as he pastured the donkeys of Zibeon his
        father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'These are the children of Anah: Dishon and Oholibamah the daughter
        of Anah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'These are the sons of Dishon: Hemdan, Eshban, Ithran, and Cheran. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'These are the sons of Ezer: Bilhan, Zaavan, and Akan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'These are the sons of Dishan: Uz and Aran. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'These are the chiefs of the Horites: the chiefs Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon,
        Anah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Dishon, Ezer, and Dishan; these are the chiefs of the Horites, chief
        by chief in the land of Seir.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: '  These are the kings who reigned in the land of Edom, before any
        king reigned over the Israelites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Bela the son of Beor reigned in Edom, the name of his city being
        Dinhabah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Bela died, and Jobab the son of Zerah of Bozrah reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Jobab died, and Husham of the land of the Temanites reigned in his
        place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Husham died, and Hadad the son of Bedad, who defeated Midian in the
        country of Moab, reigned in his place, the name of his city being Avith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Hadad died, and Samlah of Masrekah reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Samlah died, and Shaul of Rehoboth on the Euphrates[[COMMENT(0)]]
        reigned in his place. '
      comments:
      - number: '36:37 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Shaul died, and Baal-hanan the son of Achbor reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Baal-hanan the son of Achbor died, and Hadar reigned in his place,
        the name of his city being Pau; his wife\u2019s name was Mehetabel, the daughter
        of Matred, daughter of Mezahab.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'These are the names of the chiefs of Esau, according to their clans
        and their dwelling places, by their names: the chiefs Timna, Alvah, Jetheth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Oholibamah, Elah, Pinon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Kenaz, Teman, Mibzar, '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: Magdiel, and Iram; these are the chiefs of Edom (that is, Esau, the
        father of Edom), according to their dwelling places in the land of their
        possession.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Joseph\u2019s Dreams"
      title: "Joseph\u2019s Dreams"
      number: 1
      content: "  Jacob lived in the land of his father\u2019s sojournings, in the
        land of Canaan.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "These are the generations of Jacob.Joseph, being seventeen years
        old, was pasturing the flock with his brothers. He was a boy with the sons
        of Bilhah and Zilpah, his father\u2019s wives. And Joseph brought a bad report
        of them to their father. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now Israel loved Joseph more than any other of his sons, because
        he was the son of his old age. And he made him a robe of many colors.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '37:3 '
        content: See Septuagint, Vulgate; or (with Syriac) . The meaning of the Hebrew
          is uncertain; also verses 23, 32
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But when his brothers saw that their father loved him more than all
        his brothers, they hated him and could not speak peacefully to him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now Joseph had a dream, and when he told it to his brothers they
        hated him even more. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "He said to them, \u201CHear this dream that I have dreamed: "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Behold, we were binding sheaves in the field, and behold, my sheaf
        arose and stood upright. And behold, your sheaves gathered around it and
        bowed down to my sheaf.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "His brothers said to him, \u201CAre you indeed to reign over us?
        Or are you indeed to rule over us?\u201D So they hated him even more for
        his dreams and for his words.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then he dreamed another dream and told it to his brothers and said,
        \u201CBehold, I have dreamed another dream. Behold, the sun, the moon, and
        eleven stars were bowing down to me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But when he told it to his father and to his brothers, his father
        rebuked him and said to him, \u201CWhat is this dream that you have dreamed?
        Shall I and your mother and your brothers indeed come to bow ourselves to
        the ground before you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Joseph Sold by His Brothers'
      title: Joseph Sold by His Brothers
      number: 11
      content: 'And his brothers were jealous of him, but his father kept the saying
        in mind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Now his brothers went to pasture their father\u2019s flock near Shechem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Israel said to Joseph, \u201CAre not your brothers pasturing
        the flock at Shechem? Come, I will send you to them.\u201D And he said to
        him, \u201CHere I am.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So he said to him, \u201CGo now, see if it is well with your brothers
        and with the flock, and bring me word.\u201D So he sent him from the Valley
        of Hebron, and he came to Shechem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And a man found him wandering in the fields. And the man asked him,
        \u201CWhat are you seeking?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CI am seeking my brothers,\u201D he said. \u201CTell me, please,
        where they are pasturing the flock.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And the man said, \u201CThey have gone away, for I heard them say,
        \u2018Let us go to Dothan.\u2019\u201D So Joseph went after his brothers
        and found them at Dothan.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'They saw him from afar, and before he came near to them they conspired
        against him to kill him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "They said to one another, \u201CHere comes this dreamer. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Come now, let us kill him and throw him into one of the pits.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Then we will say that a fierce animal has devoured him, and we will see what
        will become of his dreams.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '37:20 '
        content: Or ; also verses 22, 24
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But when Reuben heard it, he rescued him out of their hands, saying,
        \u201CLet us not take his life.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And Reuben said to them, \u201CShed no blood; throw him into this
        pit here in the wilderness, but do not lay a hand on him\u201D\u2014that
        he might rescue him out of their hand to restore him to his father. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So when Joseph came to his brothers, they stripped him of his robe,
        the robe of many colors that he wore. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And they took him and threw him into a pit. The pit was empty; there
        was no water in it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then they sat down to eat. And looking up they saw a caravan of Ishmaelites
        coming from Gilead, with their camels bearing gum, balm, and myrrh, on their
        way to carry it down to Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then Judah said to his brothers, \u201CWhat profit is it if we kill
        our brother and conceal his blood? "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Come, let us sell him to the Ishmaelites, and let not our hand be
        upon him, for he is our brother, our own flesh.\u201D And his brothers listened
        to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then Midianite traders passed by. And they drew Joseph up and lifted
        him out of the pit, and sold him to the Ishmaelites for twenty shekels[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of silver. They took Joseph to Egypt.  '
      comments:
      - number: '37:28 '
        content: A was about 2/5 ounce or 11 grams
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'When Reuben returned to the pit and saw that Joseph was not in the
        pit, he tore his clothes '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "and returned to his brothers and said, \u201CThe boy is gone, and
        I, where shall I go?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then they took Joseph\u2019s robe and slaughtered a goat and dipped
        the robe in the blood. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And they sent the robe of many colors and brought it to their father
        and said, \u201CThis we have found; please identify whether it is your son\u2019s
        robe or not.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And he identified it and said, \u201CIt is my son\u2019s robe. A
        fierce animal has devoured him. Joseph is without doubt torn to pieces.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Then Jacob tore his garments and put sackcloth on his loins and mourned
        for his son many days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "All his sons and all his daughters rose up to comfort him, but he
        refused to be comforted and said, \u201CNo, I shall go down to Sheol to my
        son, mourning.\u201D Thus his father wept for him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: Meanwhile the Midianites had sold him in Egypt to Potiphar, an officer
        of Pharaoh, the captain of the guard.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judah and Tamar'
      title: Judah and Tamar
      number: 1
      content: '  It happened at that time that Judah went down from his brothers
        and turned aside to a certain Adullamite, whose name was Hirah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'There Judah saw the daughter of a certain Canaanite whose name was
        Shua. He took her and went in to her, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and she conceived and bore a son, and he called his name Er. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'She conceived again and bore a son, and she called his name Onan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Yet again she bore a son, and she called his name Shelah. Judah[[COMMENT(0)]]
        was in Chezib when she bore him.  '
      comments:
      - number: '38:5 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Judah took a wife for Er his firstborn, and her name was Tamar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But Er, Judah\u2019s firstborn, was wicked in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> put him to death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Judah said to Onan, \u201CGo in to your brother\u2019s wife
        and perform the duty of a brother-in-law to her, and raise up offspring for
        your brother.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But Onan knew that the offspring would not be his. So whenever he
        went in to his brother\u2019s wife he would waste the semen on the ground,
        so as not to give offspring to his brother. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And what he did was wicked in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and he put him to death also. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Judah said to Tamar his daughter-in-law, \u201CRemain a widow
        in your father\u2019s house, till Shelah my son grows up\u201D\u2014for he
        feared that he would die, like his brothers. So Tamar went and remained in
        her father\u2019s house.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "In the course of time the wife of Judah, Shua\u2019s daughter, died.
        When Judah was comforted, he went up to Timnah to his sheepshearers, he and
        his friend Hirah the Adullamite. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And when Tamar was told, \u201CYour father-in-law is going up to
        Timnah to shear his sheep,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "she took off her widow\u2019s garments and covered herself with a
        veil, wrapping herself up, and sat at the entrance to Enaim, which is on
        the road to Timnah. For she saw that Shelah was grown up, and she had not
        been given to him in marriage. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When Judah saw her, he thought she was a prostitute, for she had
        covered her face. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He turned to her at the roadside and said, \u201CCome, let me come
        in to you,\u201D for he did not know that she was his daughter-in-law. She
        said, \u201CWhat will you give me, that you may come in to me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "He answered, \u201CI will send you a young goat from the flock.\u201D
        And she said, \u201CIf you give me a pledge, until you send it\u2014\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "He said, \u201CWhat pledge shall I give you?\u201D She replied, \u201CYour
        signet and your cord and your staff that is in your hand.\u201D So he gave
        them to her and went in to her, and she conceived by him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then she arose and went away, and taking off her veil she put on
        the garments of her widowhood.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "When Judah sent the young goat by his friend the Adullamite to take
        back the pledge from the woman\u2019s hand, he did not find her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And he asked the men of the place, \u201CWhere is the cult prostitute[[COMMENT(0)]]
        who was at Enaim at the roadside?\u201D And they said, \u201CNo cult prostitute
        has been here.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '38:21 '
        content: Hebrew ; a woman who served a pagan deity by prostitution; also
          verse 22
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So he returned to Judah and said, \u201CI have not found her. Also,
        the men of the place said, \u2018No cult prostitute has been here.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And Judah replied, \u201CLet her keep the things as her own, or we
        shall be laughed at. You see, I sent this young goat, and you did not find
        her.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "About three months later Judah was told, \u201CTamar your daughter-in-law
        has been immoral.[[COMMENT(0)]] Moreover, she is pregnant by immorality.\u201D
        And Judah said, \u201CBring her out, and let her be burned.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '38:24 '
        content: 'Or Or '
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "As she was being brought out, she sent word to her father-in-law,
        \u201CBy the man to whom these belong, I am pregnant.\u201D And she said,
        \u201CPlease identify whose these are, the signet and the cord and the staff.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then Judah identified them and said, \u201CShe is more righteous
        than I, since I did not give her to my son Shelah.\u201D And he did not know
        her again.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'When the time of her labor came, there were twins in her womb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And when she was in labor, one put out a hand, and the midwife took
        and tied a scarlet thread on his hand, saying, \u201CThis one came out first.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "But as he drew back his hand, behold, his brother came out. And she
        said, \u201CWhat a breach you have made for yourself!\u201D Therefore his
        name was called Perez.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '38:29 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Afterward his brother came out with the scarlet thread on his hand,
        and his name was called Zerah.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Joseph and Potiphar\u2019s Wife"
      title: "Joseph and Potiphar\u2019s Wife"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Joseph had been brought down to Egypt, and Potiphar, an officer
        of Pharaoh, the captain of the guard, an Egyptian, had bought him from the
        Ishmaelites who had brought him down there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was with Joseph, and he became a
        successful man, and he was in the house of his Egyptian master. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'His master saw that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was with him
        and that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  caused all that he did to succeed
        in his hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So Joseph found favor in his sight and attended him, and he made
        him overseer of his house and put him in charge of all that he had. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "From the time that he made him overseer in his house and over all
        that he had, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> blessed the Egyptian\u2019s
        house for Joseph\u2019s sake; the blessing of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        was on all that he had, in house and field. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So he left all that he had in Joseph\u2019s charge, and because of
        him he had no concern about anything but the food he ate.Now Joseph was handsome
        in form and appearance. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And after a time his master\u2019s wife cast her eyes on Joseph and
        said, \u201CLie with me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But he refused and said to his master\u2019s wife, \u201CBehold,
        because of me my master has no concern about anything in the house, and he
        has put everything that he has in my charge. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He is not greater in this house than I am, nor has he kept back anything
        from me except you, because you are his wife. How then can I do this great
        wickedness and sin against God?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And as she spoke to Joseph day after day, he would not listen to
        her, to lie beside her or to be with her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But one day, when he went into the house to do his work and none
        of the men of the house was there in the house, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "she caught him by his garment, saying, \u201CLie with me.\u201D But
        he left his garment in her hand and fled and got out of the house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And as soon as she saw that he had left his garment in her hand and
        had fled out of the house, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "she called to the men of her household and said to them, \u201CSee,
        he has brought among us a Hebrew to laugh at us. He came in to me to lie
        with me, and I cried out with a loud voice. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And as soon as he heard that I lifted up my voice and cried out,
        he left his garment beside me and fled and got out of the house.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then she laid up his garment by her until his master came home, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "and she told him the same story, saying, \u201CThe Hebrew servant,
        whom you have brought among us, came in to me to laugh at me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But as soon as I lifted up my voice and cried, he left his garment
        beside me and fled out of the house.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "As soon as his master heard the words that his wife spoke to him,
        \u201CThis is the way your servant treated me,\u201D his anger was kindled. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Joseph\u2019s master took him and put him into the prison, the
        place where the king\u2019s prisoners were confined, and he was there in
        prison. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was with Joseph and showed him
        steadfast love and gave him favor in the sight of the keeper of the prison. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And the keeper of the prison put Joseph in charge of all the prisoners
        who were in the prison. Whatever was done there, he was the one who did it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The keeper of the prison paid no attention to anything that was in
        Joseph\u2019s charge, because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was with him.
        And whatever he did, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> made it succeed."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Joseph Interprets Two Prisoners\u2019 Dreams"
      title: "Joseph Interprets Two Prisoners\u2019 Dreams"
      number: 1
      content: '  Some time after this, the cupbearer of the king of Egypt and his
        baker committed an offense against their lord the king of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Pharaoh was angry with his two officers, the chief cupbearer
        and the chief baker, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and he put them in custody in the house of the captain of the guard,
        in the prison where Joseph was confined. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The captain of the guard appointed Joseph to be with them, and he
        attended them. They continued for some time in custody.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And one night they both dreamed\u2014the cupbearer and the baker
        of the king of Egypt, who were confined in the prison\u2014each his own dream,
        and each dream with its own interpretation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When Joseph came to them in the morning, he saw that they were troubled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So he asked Pharaoh\u2019s officers who were with him in custody
        in his master\u2019s house, \u201CWhy are your faces downcast today?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "They said to him, \u201CWe have had dreams, and there is no one to
        interpret them.\u201D And Joseph said to them, \u201CDo not interpretations
        belong to God? Please tell them to me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So the chief cupbearer told his dream to Joseph and said to him,
        \u201CIn my dream there was a vine before me, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and on the vine there were three branches. As soon as it budded,
        its blossoms shot forth, and the clusters ripened into grapes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Pharaoh\u2019s cup was in my hand, and I took the grapes and pressed
        them into Pharaoh\u2019s cup and placed the cup in Pharaoh\u2019s hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Joseph said to him, \u201CThis is its interpretation: the three
        branches are three days. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "In three days Pharaoh will lift up your head and restore you to your
        office, and you shall place Pharaoh\u2019s cup in his hand as formerly, when
        you were his cupbearer. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Only remember me, when it is well with you, and please do me the
        kindness to mention me to Pharaoh, and so get me out of this house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For I was indeed stolen out of the land of the Hebrews, and here
        also I have done nothing that they should put me into the pit.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When the chief baker saw that the interpretation was favorable, he
        said to Joseph, \u201CI also had a dream: there were three cake baskets on
        my head, "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "and in the uppermost basket there were all sorts of baked food for
        Pharaoh, but the birds were eating it out of the basket on my head.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Joseph answered and said, \u201CThis is its interpretation: the
        three baskets are three days. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "In three days Pharaoh will lift up your head\u2014from you!\u2014and
        hang you on a tree. And the birds will eat the flesh from you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "On the third day, which was Pharaoh\u2019s birthday, he made a feast
        for all his servants and lifted up the head of the chief cupbearer and the
        head of the chief baker among his servants. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "He restored the chief cupbearer to his position, and he placed the
        cup in Pharaoh\u2019s hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But he hanged the chief baker, as Joseph had interpreted to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Yet the chief cupbearer did not remember Joseph, but forgot him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Joseph Interprets Pharaoh\u2019s Dreams"
      title: "Joseph Interprets Pharaoh\u2019s Dreams"
      number: 1
      content: '  After two whole years, Pharaoh dreamed that he was standing by
        the Nile, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and behold, there came up out of the Nile seven cows, attractive
        and plump, and they fed in the reed grass. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And behold, seven other cows, ugly and thin, came up out of the Nile
        after them, and stood by the other cows on the bank of the Nile. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the ugly, thin cows ate up the seven attractive, plump cows.
        And Pharaoh awoke. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And he fell asleep and dreamed a second time. And behold, seven ears
        of grain, plump and good, were growing on one stalk. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And behold, after them sprouted seven ears, thin and blighted by
        the east wind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the thin ears swallowed up the seven plump, full ears. And Pharaoh
        awoke, and behold, it was a dream. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So in the morning his spirit was troubled, and he sent and called
        for all the magicians of Egypt and all its wise men. Pharaoh told them his
        dreams, but there was none who could interpret them to Pharaoh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the chief cupbearer said to Pharaoh, \u201CI remember my offenses
        today. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'When Pharaoh was angry with his servants and put me and the chief
        baker in custody in the house of the captain of the guard, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'we dreamed on the same night, he and I, each having a dream with
        its own interpretation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'A young Hebrew was there with us, a servant of the captain of the
        guard. When we told him, he interpreted our dreams to us, giving an interpretation
        to each man according to his dream. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And as he interpreted to us, so it came about. I was restored to
        my office, and the baker was hanged.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  Then Pharaoh sent and called Joseph, and they quickly brought him
        out of the pit. And when he had shaved himself and changed his clothes, he
        came in before Pharaoh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And Pharaoh said to Joseph, \u201CI have had a dream, and there is
        no one who can interpret it. I have heard it said of you that when you hear
        a dream you can interpret it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Joseph answered Pharaoh, \u201CIt is not in me; God will give Pharaoh
        a favorable answer.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '41:16 '
        content: 'Or (compare Samaritan, Septuagint) '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Pharaoh said to Joseph, \u201CBehold, in my dream I was standing
        on the banks of the Nile. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Seven cows, plump and attractive, came up out of the Nile and fed
        in the reed grass. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Seven other cows came up after them, poor and very ugly and thin,
        such as I had never seen in all the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the thin, ugly cows ate up the first seven plump cows, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'but when they had eaten them no one would have known that they had
        eaten them, for they were still as ugly as at the beginning. Then I awoke. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'I also saw in my dream seven ears growing on one stalk, full and
        good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Seven ears, withered, thin, and blighted by the east wind, sprouted
        after them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "and the thin ears swallowed up the seven good ears. And I told it
        to the magicians, but there was no one who could explain it to me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Joseph said to Pharaoh, \u201CThe dreams of Pharaoh are one;
        God has revealed to Pharaoh what he is about to do. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The seven good cows are seven years, and the seven good ears are
        seven years; the dreams are one. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The seven lean and ugly cows that came up after them are seven years,
        and the seven empty ears blighted by the east wind are also seven years of
        famine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'It is as I told Pharaoh; God has shown to Pharaoh what he is about
        to do. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'There will come seven years of great plenty throughout all the land
        of Egypt, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'but after them there will arise seven years of famine, and all the
        plenty will be forgotten in the land of Egypt. The famine will consume the
        land, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'and the plenty will be unknown in the land by reason of the famine
        that will follow, for it will be very severe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And the doubling of Pharaoh\u2019s dream means that the thing is
        fixed by God, and God will shortly bring it about. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Now therefore let Pharaoh select a discerning and wise man, and set
        him over the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Let Pharaoh proceed to appoint overseers over the land and take one-fifth
        of the produce of the land[[COMMENT(0)]] of Egypt during the seven plentiful
        years. '
      comments:
      - number: '41:34 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And let them gather all the food of these good years that are coming
        and store up grain under the authority of Pharaoh for food in the cities,
        and let them keep it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: Joseph Rises to Power'
      title: Joseph Rises to Power
      number: 36
      content: "That food shall be a reserve for the land against the seven years
        of famine that are to occur in the land of Egypt, so that the land may not
        perish through the famine.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'This proposal pleased Pharaoh and all his servants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "And Pharaoh said to his servants, \u201CCan we find a man like this,
        in whom is the Spirit of God?\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '41:38 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Then Pharaoh said to Joseph, \u201CSince God has shown you all this,
        there is none so discerning and wise as you are. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "You shall be over my house, and all my people shall order themselves
        as you command.[[COMMENT(0)]] Only as regards the throne will I be greater
        than you.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '41:40 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "And Pharaoh said to Joseph, \u201CSee, I have set you over all the
        land of Egypt.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Then Pharaoh took his signet ring from his hand and put it on Joseph\u2019s
        hand, and clothed him in garments of fine linen and put a gold chain about
        his neck. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "And he made him ride in his second chariot. And they called out before
        him, \u201CBow the knee!\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]] Thus he set him over all the
        land of Egypt. "
      comments:
      - number: '41:43 '
        content: ', probably an Egyptian word, similar in sound to the Hebrew word
          meaning '
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "Moreover, Pharaoh said to Joseph, \u201CI am Pharaoh, and without
        your consent no one shall lift up hand or foot in all the land of Egypt.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "And Pharaoh called Joseph\u2019s name Zaphenath-paneah. And he gave
        him in marriage Asenath, the daughter of Potiphera priest of On. So Joseph
        went out over the land of Egypt.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Joseph was thirty years old when he entered the service of Pharaoh
        king of Egypt. And Joseph went out from the presence of Pharaoh and went
        through all the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'During the seven plentiful years the earth produced abundantly, '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'and he gathered up all the food of these seven years, which occurred
        in the land of Egypt, and put the food in the cities. He put in every city
        the food from the fields around it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'And Joseph stored up grain in great abundance, like the sand of the
        sea, until he ceased to measure it, for it could not be measured.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'Before the year of famine came, two sons were born to Joseph. Asenath,
        the daughter of Potiphera priest of On, bore them to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "Joseph called the name of the firstborn Manasseh. \u201CFor,\u201D
        he said, \u201CGod has made me forget all my hardship and all my father\u2019s
        house.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '41:51 '
        content: 'sounds like the Hebrew for '
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "The name of the second he called Ephraim, \u201CFor God has made
        me fruitful in the land of my affliction.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '41:52 '
        content: 'sounds like the Hebrew for '
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'The seven years of plenty that occurred in the land of Egypt came
        to an end, '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'and the seven years of famine began to come, as Joseph had said.
        There was famine in all lands, but in all the land of Egypt there was bread. '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: "When all the land of Egypt was famished, the people cried to Pharaoh
        for bread. Pharaoh said to all the Egyptians, \u201CGo to Joseph. What he
        says to you, do.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'So when the famine had spread over all the land, Joseph opened all
        the storehouses[[COMMENT(0)]] and sold to the Egyptians, for the famine was
        severe in the land of Egypt. '
      comments:
      - number: '41:56 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: Moreover, all the earth came to Egypt to Joseph to buy grain, because
        the famine was severe over all the earth.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Joseph\u2019s Brothers Go to Egypt"
      title: "Joseph\u2019s Brothers Go to Egypt"
      number: 1
      content: "  When Jacob learned that there was grain for sale in Egypt, he said
        to his sons, \u201CWhy do you look at one another?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he said, \u201CBehold, I have heard that there is grain for sale
        in Egypt. Go down and buy grain for us there, that we may live and not die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So ten of Joseph\u2019s brothers went down to buy grain in Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But Jacob did not send Benjamin, Joseph\u2019s brother, with his
        brothers, for he feared that harm might happen to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Thus the sons of Israel came to buy among the others who came, for
        the famine was in the land of Canaan.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Now Joseph was governor over the land. He was the one who sold to
        all the people of the land. And Joseph\u2019s brothers came and bowed themselves
        before him with their faces to the ground. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Joseph saw his brothers and recognized them, but he treated them
        like strangers and spoke roughly to them. \u201CWhere do you come from?\u201D
        he said. They said, \u201CFrom the land of Canaan, to buy food.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And Joseph recognized his brothers, but they did not recognize him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Joseph remembered the dreams that he had dreamed of them. And
        he said to them, \u201CYou are spies; you have come to see the nakedness
        of the land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "They said to him, \u201CNo, my lord, your servants have come to buy
        food. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "We are all sons of one man. We are honest men. Your servants have
        never been spies.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "He said to them, \u201CNo, it is the nakedness of the land that you
        have come to see.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And they said, \u201CWe, your servants, are twelve brothers, the
        sons of one man in the land of Canaan, and behold, the youngest is this day
        with our father, and one is no more.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But Joseph said to them, \u201CIt is as I said to you. You are spies. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'By this you shall be tested: by the life of Pharaoh, you shall not
        go from this place unless your youngest brother comes here. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Send one of you, and let him bring your brother, while you remain
        confined, that your words may be tested, whether there is truth in you. Or
        else, by the life of Pharaoh, surely you are spies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And he put them all together in custody for three days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "On the third day Joseph said to them, \u201CDo this and you will
        live, for I fear God: "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'if you are honest men, let one of your brothers remain confined where
        you are in custody, and let the rest go and carry grain for the famine of
        your households, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "and bring your youngest brother to me. So your words will be verified,
        and you shall not die.\u201D And they did so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then they said to one another, \u201CIn truth we are guilty concerning
        our brother, in that we saw the distress of his soul, when he begged us and
        we did not listen. That is why this distress has come upon us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And Reuben answered them, \u201CDid I not tell you not to sin against
        the boy? But you did not listen. So now there comes a reckoning for his blood.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'They did not know that Joseph understood them, for there was an interpreter
        between them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then he turned away from them and wept. And he returned to them and
        spoke to them. And he took Simeon from them and bound him before their eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And Joseph gave orders to fill their bags with grain, and to replace
        every man\u2019s money in his sack, and to give them provisions for the journey.
        This was done for them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then they loaded their donkeys with their grain and departed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And as one of them opened his sack to give his donkey fodder at the
        lodging place, he saw his money in the mouth of his sack. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "He said to his brothers, \u201CMy money has been put back; here it
        is in the mouth of my sack!\u201D At this their hearts failed them, and they
        turned trembling to one another, saying, \u201CWhat is this that God has
        done to us?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'When they came to Jacob their father in the land of Canaan, they
        told him all that had happened to them, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CThe man, the lord of the land, spoke roughly to us and took
        us to be spies of the land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "But we said to him, \u2018We are honest men; we have never been spies. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "We are twelve brothers, sons of our father. One is no more, and the
        youngest is this day with our father in the land of Canaan.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then the man, the lord of the land, said to us, \u2018By this I shall
        know that you are honest men: leave one of your brothers with me, and take
        grain for the famine of your households, and go your way. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Bring your youngest brother to me. Then I shall know that you are
        not spies but honest men, and I will deliver your brother to you, and you
        shall trade in the land.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "  As they emptied their sacks, behold, every man\u2019s bundle of
        money was in his sack. And when they and their father saw their bundles of
        money, they were afraid. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And Jacob their father said to them, \u201CYou have bereaved me of
        my children: Joseph is no more, and Simeon is no more, and now you would
        take Benjamin. All this has come against me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Then Reuben said to his father, \u201CKill my two sons if I do not
        bring him back to you. Put him in my hands, and I will bring him back to
        you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "But he said, \u201CMy son shall not go down with you, for his brother
        is dead, and he is the only one left. If harm should happen to him on the
        journey that you are to make, you would bring down my gray hairs with sorrow
        to Sheol.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Joseph\u2019s Brothers Return to Egypt"
      title: "Joseph\u2019s Brothers Return to Egypt"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the famine was severe in the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And when they had eaten the grain that they had brought from Egypt,
        their father said to them, \u201CGo again, buy us a little food.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But Judah said to him, \u201CThe man solemnly warned us, saying,
        \u2018You shall not see my face unless your brother is with you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'If you will send our brother with us, we will go down and buy you
        food. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But if you will not send him, we will not go down, for the man said
        to us, \u2018You shall not see my face, unless your brother is with you.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Israel said, \u201CWhy did you treat me so badly as to tell the man
        that you had another brother?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "They replied, \u201CThe man questioned us carefully about ourselves
        and our kindred, saying, \u2018Is your father still alive? Do you have another
        brother?\u2019 What we told him was in answer to these questions. Could we
        in any way know that he would say, \u2018Bring your brother down\u2019?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Judah said to Israel his father, \u201CSend the boy with me,
        and we will arise and go, that we may live and not die, both we and you and
        also our little ones. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I will be a pledge of his safety. From my hand you shall require
        him. If I do not bring him back to you and set him before you, then let me
        bear the blame forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "If we had not delayed, we would now have returned twice.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then their father Israel said to them, \u201CIf it must be so, then
        do this: take some of the choice fruits of the land in your bags, and carry
        a present down to the man, a little balm and a little honey, gum, myrrh,
        pistachio nuts, and almonds. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Take double the money with you. Carry back with you the money that
        was returned in the mouth of your sacks. Perhaps it was an oversight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Take also your brother, and arise, go again to the man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "May God Almighty[[COMMENT(0)]]  grant you mercy before the man, and
        may he send back your other brother and Benjamin. And as for me, if I am
        bereaved of my children, I am bereaved.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '43:14 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So the men took this present, and they took double the money with
        them, and Benjamin. They arose and went down to Egypt and stood before Joseph.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When Joseph saw Benjamin with them, he said to the steward of his
        house, \u201CBring the men into the house, and slaughter an animal and make
        ready, for the men are to dine with me at noon.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The man did as Joseph told him and brought the men to Joseph\u2019s
        house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And the men were afraid because they were brought to Joseph\u2019s
        house, and they said, \u201CIt is because of the money, which was replaced
        in our sacks the first time, that we are brought in, so that he may assault
        us and fall upon us to make us servants and seize our donkeys.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So they went up to the steward of Joseph\u2019s house and spoke with
        him at the door of the house, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "and said, \u201COh, my lord, we came down the first time to buy food. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And when we came to the lodging place we opened our sacks, and there
        was each man\u2019s money in the mouth of his sack, our money in full weight.
        So we have brought it again with us, "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "and we have brought other money down with us to buy food. We do not
        know who put our money in our sacks.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "He replied, \u201CPeace to you, do not be afraid. Your God and the
        God of your father has put treasure in your sacks for you. I received your
        money.\u201D Then he brought Simeon out to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And when the man had brought the men into Joseph\u2019s house and
        given them water, and they had washed their feet, and when he had given their
        donkeys fodder, "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "they prepared the present for Joseph\u2019s coming at noon, for they
        heard that they should eat bread there.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'When Joseph came home, they brought into the house to him the present
        that they had with them and bowed down to him to the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And he inquired about their welfare and said, \u201CIs your father
        well, the old man of whom you spoke? Is he still alive?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "They said, \u201CYour servant our father is well; he is still alive.\u201D
        And they bowed their heads and prostrated themselves. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And he lifted up his eyes and saw his brother Benjamin, his mother\u2019s
        son, and said, \u201CIs this your youngest brother, of whom you spoke to
        me? God be gracious to you, my son!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then Joseph hurried out, for his compassion grew warm for his brother,
        and he sought a place to weep. And he entered his chamber and wept there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then he washed his face and came out. And controlling himself he
        said, \u201CServe the food.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'They served him by himself, and them by themselves, and the Egyptians
        who ate with him by themselves, because the Egyptians could not eat with
        the Hebrews, for that is an abomination to the Egyptians. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And they sat before him, the firstborn according to his birthright
        and the youngest according to his youth. And the men looked at one another
        in amazement. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Portions were taken to them from Joseph\u2019s table, but Benjamin\u2019s
        portion was five times as much as any of theirs. And they drank and were
        merry[[COMMENT(0)]] with him."
      comments:
      - number: '43:34 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Joseph Tests His Brothers'
      title: Joseph Tests His Brothers
      number: 1
      content: "  Then he commanded the steward of his house, \u201CFill the men\u2019s
        sacks with food, as much as they can carry, and put each man\u2019s money
        in the mouth of his sack, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and put my cup, the silver cup, in the mouth of the sack of the youngest,
        with his money for the grain.\u201D And he did as Joseph told him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'As soon as the morning was light, the men were sent away with their
        donkeys. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "They had gone only a short distance from the city. Now Joseph said
        to his steward, \u201CUp, follow after the men, and when you overtake them,
        say to them, \u2018Why have you repaid evil for good?[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '44:4 '
        content: 'Septuagint (compare Vulgate) adds '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Is it not from this that my lord drinks, and by this that he practices
        divination? You have done evil in doing this.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When he overtook them, he spoke to them these words. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "They said to him, \u201CWhy does my lord speak such words as these?
        Far be it from your servants to do such a thing! "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Behold, the money that we found in the mouths of our sacks we brought
        back to you from the land of Canaan. How then could we steal silver or gold
        from your lord\u2019s house? "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Whichever of your servants is found with it shall die, and we also
        will be my lord\u2019s servants.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "He said, \u201CLet it be as you say: he who is found with it shall
        be my servant, and the rest of you shall be innocent.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then each man quickly lowered his sack to the ground, and each man
        opened his sack. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And he searched, beginning with the eldest and ending with the youngest.
        And the cup was found in Benjamin\u2019s sack. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then they tore their clothes, and every man loaded his donkey, and
        they returned to the city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "When Judah and his brothers came to Joseph\u2019s house, he was still
        there. They fell before him to the ground. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Joseph said to them, \u201CWhat deed is this that you have done?
        Do you not know that a man like me can indeed practice divination?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And Judah said, \u201CWhat shall we say to my lord? What shall we
        speak? Or how can we clear ourselves? God has found out the guilt of your
        servants; behold, we are my lord\u2019s servants, both we and he also in
        whose hand the cup has been found.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But he said, \u201CFar be it from me that I should do so! Only the
        man in whose hand the cup was found shall be my servant. But as for you,
        go up in peace to your father.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Judah went up to him and said, \u201COh, my lord, please let
        your servant speak a word in my lord\u2019s ears, and let not your anger
        burn against your servant, for you are like Pharaoh himself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "My lord asked his servants, saying, \u2018Have you a father, or a
        brother?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And we said to my lord, \u2018We have a father, an old man, and a
        young brother, the child of his old age. His brother is dead, and he alone
        is left of his mother\u2019s children, and his father loves him.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then you said to your servants, \u2018Bring him down to me, that
        I may set my eyes on him.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "We said to my lord, \u2018The boy cannot leave his father, for if
        he should leave his father, his father would die.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then you said to your servants, \u2018Unless your youngest brother
        comes down with you, you shall not see my face again.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CWhen we went back to your servant my father, we told him the
        words of my lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And when our father said, \u2018Go again, buy us a little food,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "we said, \u2018We cannot go down. If our youngest brother goes with
        us, then we will go down. For we cannot see the man\u2019s face unless our
        youngest brother is with us.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then your servant my father said to us, \u2018You know that my wife
        bore me two sons. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "One left me, and I said, \u201CSurely he has been torn to pieces,\u201D
        and I have never seen him since. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "If you take this one also from me, and harm happens to him, you will
        bring down my gray hairs in evil to Sheol.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CNow therefore, as soon as I come to your servant my father,
        and the boy is not with us, then, as his life is bound up in the boy\u2019s
        life, "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'as soon as he sees that the boy is not with us, he will die, and
        your servants will bring down the gray hairs of your servant our father with
        sorrow to Sheol. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "For your servant became a pledge of safety for the boy to my father,
        saying, \u2018If I do not bring him back to you, then I shall bear the blame
        before my father all my life.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Now therefore, please let your servant remain instead of the boy
        as a servant to my lord, and let the boy go back with his brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "For how can I go back to my father if the boy is not with me? I fear
        to see the evil that would find my father.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Joseph Provides for His Brothers and Family'
      title: Joseph Provides for His Brothers and Family
      number: 1
      content: "  Then Joseph could not control himself before all those who stood
        by him. He cried, \u201CMake everyone go out from me.\u201D So no one stayed
        with him when Joseph made himself known to his brothers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he wept aloud, so that the Egyptians heard it, and the household
        of Pharaoh heard it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And Joseph said to his brothers, \u201CI am Joseph! Is my father
        still alive?\u201D But his brothers could not answer him, for they were dismayed
        at his presence.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So Joseph said to his brothers, \u201CCome near to me, please.\u201D
        And they came near. And he said, \u201CI am your brother, Joseph, whom you
        sold into Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And now do not be distressed or angry with yourselves because you
        sold me here, for God sent me before you to preserve life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For the famine has been in the land these two years, and there are
        yet five years in which there will be neither plowing nor harvest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And God sent me before you to preserve for you a remnant on earth,
        and to keep alive for you many survivors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So it was not you who sent me here, but God. He has made me a father
        to Pharaoh, and lord of all his house and ruler over all the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Hurry and go up to my father and say to him, \u2018Thus says your
        son Joseph, God has made me lord of all Egypt. Come down to me; do not tarry. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "You shall dwell in the land of Goshen, and you shall be near me,
        you and your children and your children\u2019s children, and your flocks,
        your herds, and all that you have. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "There I will provide for you, for there are yet five years of famine
        to come, so that you and your household, and all that you have, do not come
        to poverty.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And now your eyes see, and the eyes of my brother Benjamin see, that
        it is my mouth that speaks to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "You must tell my father of all my honor in Egypt, and of all that
        you have seen. Hurry and bring my father down here.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then he fell upon his brother Benjamin\u2019s neck and wept, and
        Benjamin wept upon his neck. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And he kissed all his brothers and wept upon them. After that his
        brothers talked with him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When the report was heard in Pharaoh\u2019s house, \u201CJoseph\u2019s
        brothers have come,\u201D it pleased Pharaoh and his servants. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And Pharaoh said to Joseph, \u201CSay to your brothers, \u2018Do
        this: load your beasts and go back to the land of Canaan, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "and take your father and your households, and come to me, and I will
        give you the best of the land of Egypt, and you shall eat the fat of the
        land.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And you, Joseph, are commanded to say, \u2018Do this: take wagons
        from the land of Egypt for your little ones and for your wives, and bring
        your father, and come. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Have no concern for[[COMMENT(0)]] your goods, for the best of all
        the land of Egypt is yours.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '45:20 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The sons of Israel did so: and Joseph gave them wagons, according
        to the command of Pharaoh, and gave them provisions for the journey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'To each and all of them he gave a change of clothes, but to Benjamin
        he gave three hundred shekels[[COMMENT(0)]] of silver and five changes of
        clothes. '
      comments:
      - number: '45:22 '
        content: A was about 2/5 ounce or 11 grams
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'To his father he sent as follows: ten donkeys loaded with the good
        things of Egypt, and ten female donkeys loaded with grain, bread, and provision
        for his father on the journey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then he sent his brothers away, and as they departed, he said to
        them, \u201CDo not quarrel on the way.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So they went up out of Egypt and came to the land of Canaan to their
        father Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And they told him, \u201CJoseph is still alive, and he is ruler over
        all the land of Egypt.\u201D And his heart became numb, for he did not believe
        them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'But when they told him all the words of Joseph, which he had said
        to them, and when he saw the wagons that Joseph had sent to carry him, the
        spirit of their father Jacob revived. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And Israel said, \u201CIt is enough; Joseph my son is still alive.
        I will go and see him before I die.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Joseph Brings His Family to Egypt'
      title: Joseph Brings His Family to Egypt
      number: 1
      content: '  So Israel took his journey with all that he had and came to Beersheba,
        and offered sacrifices to the God of his father Isaac. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And God spoke to Israel in visions of the night and said, \u201CJacob,
        Jacob.\u201D And he said, \u201CHere I am.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then he said, \u201CI am God, the God of your father. Do not be afraid
        to go down to Egypt, for there I will make you into a great nation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "I myself will go down with you to Egypt, and I will also bring you
        up again, and Joseph\u2019s hand shall close your eyes.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then Jacob set out from Beersheba. The sons of Israel carried Jacob
        their father, their little ones, and their wives, in the wagons that Pharaoh
        had sent to carry him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'They also took their livestock and their goods, which they had gained
        in the land of Canaan, and came into Egypt, Jacob and all his offspring with
        him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "his sons, and his sons\u2019 sons with him, his daughters, and his
        sons\u2019 daughters. All his offspring he brought with him into Egypt.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "  Now these are the names of the descendants of Israel, who came
        into Egypt, Jacob and his sons. Reuben, Jacob\u2019s firstborn, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'and the sons of Reuben: Hanoch, Pallu, Hezron, and Carmi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The sons of Simeon: Jemuel, Jamin, Ohad, Jachin, Zohar, and Shaul,
        the son of a Canaanite woman. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The sons of Levi: Gershon, Kohath, and Merari. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The sons of Judah: Er, Onan, Shelah, Perez, and Zerah (but Er and
        Onan died in the land of Canaan); and the sons of Perez were Hezron and Hamul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The sons of Issachar: Tola, Puvah, Yob, and Shimron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The sons of Zebulun: Sered, Elon, and Jahleel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'These are the sons of Leah, whom she bore to Jacob in Paddan-aram,
        together with his daughter Dinah; altogether his sons and his daughters numbered
        thirty-three.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The sons of Gad: Ziphion, Haggi, Shuni, Ezbon, Eri, Arodi, and Areli. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The sons of Asher: Imnah, Ishvah, Ishvi, Beriah, with Serah their
        sister. And the sons of Beriah: Heber and Malchiel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "These are the sons of Zilpah, whom Laban gave to Leah his daughter;
        and these she bore to Jacob\u2014sixteen persons.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "The sons of Rachel, Jacob\u2019s wife: Joseph and Benjamin. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And to Joseph in the land of Egypt were born Manasseh and Ephraim,
        whom Asenath, the daughter of Potiphera the priest of On, bore to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And the sons of Benjamin: Bela, Becher, Ashbel, Gera, Naaman, Ehi,
        Rosh, Muppim, Huppim, and Ard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "These are the sons of Rachel, who were born to Jacob\u2014fourteen
        persons in all.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The son[[COMMENT(0)]] of Dan: Hushim. '
      comments:
      - number: '46:23 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The sons of Naphtali: Jahzeel, Guni, Jezer, and Shillem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "These are the sons of Bilhah, whom Laban gave to Rachel his daughter,
        and these she bore to Jacob\u2014seven persons in all.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "All the persons belonging to Jacob who came into Egypt, who were
        his own descendants, not including Jacob\u2019s sons\u2019 wives, were sixty-six
        persons in all. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Jacob and Joseph Reunited'
      title: Jacob and Joseph Reunited
      number: 27
      content: 'And the sons of Joseph, who were born to him in Egypt, were two.
        All the persons of the house of Jacob who came into Egypt were seventy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'He had sent Judah ahead of him to Joseph to show the way before him
        in Goshen, and they came into the land of Goshen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then Joseph prepared his chariot and went up to meet Israel his father
        in Goshen. He presented himself to him and fell on his neck and wept on his
        neck a good while. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Israel said to Joseph, \u201CNow let me die, since I have seen your
        face and know that you are still alive.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Joseph said to his brothers and to his father\u2019s household, \u201CI
        will go up and tell Pharaoh and will say to him, \u2018My brothers and my
        father\u2019s household, who were in the land of Canaan, have come to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And the men are shepherds, for they have been keepers of livestock,
        and they have brought their flocks and their herds and all that they have.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "When Pharaoh calls you and says, \u2018What is your occupation?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "you shall say, \u2018Your servants have been keepers of livestock
        from our youth even until now, both we and our fathers,\u2019 in order that
        you may dwell in the land of Goshen, for every shepherd is an abomination
        to the Egyptians.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jacob\u2019s Family Settles in Goshen"
      title: "Jacob\u2019s Family Settles in Goshen"
      number: 1
      content: "  So Joseph went in and told Pharaoh, \u201CMy father and my brothers,
        with their flocks and herds and all that they possess, have come from the
        land of Canaan. They are now in the land of Goshen.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And from among his brothers he took five men and presented them to
        Pharaoh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Pharaoh said to his brothers, \u201CWhat is your occupation?\u201D
        And they said to Pharaoh, \u201CYour servants are shepherds, as our fathers
        were.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "They said to Pharaoh, \u201CWe have come to sojourn in the land,
        for there is no pasture for your servants\u2019 flocks, for the famine is
        severe in the land of Canaan. And now, please let your servants dwell in
        the land of Goshen.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Pharaoh said to Joseph, \u201CYour father and your brothers
        have come to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The land of Egypt is before you. Settle your father and your brothers
        in the best of the land. Let them settle in the land of Goshen, and if you
        know any able men among them, put them in charge of my livestock.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then Joseph brought in Jacob his father and stood him before Pharaoh,
        and Jacob blessed Pharaoh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Pharaoh said to Jacob, \u201CHow many are the days of the years
        of your life?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Jacob said to Pharaoh, \u201CThe days of the years of my sojourning
        are 130 years. Few and evil have been the days of the years of my life, and
        they have not attained to the days of the years of the life of my fathers
        in the days of their sojourning.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Jacob blessed Pharaoh and went out from the presence of Pharaoh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then Joseph settled his father and his brothers and gave them a possession
        in the land of Egypt, in the best of the land, in the land of Rameses, as
        Pharaoh had commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Joseph and the Famine'
      title: Joseph and the Famine
      number: 12
      content: "And Joseph provided his father, his brothers, and all his father\u2019s
        household with food, according to the number of their dependents.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now there was no food in all the land, for the famine was very severe,
        so that the land of Egypt and the land of Canaan languished by reason of
        the famine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And Joseph gathered up all the money that was found in the land of
        Egypt and in the land of Canaan, in exchange for the grain that they bought.
        And Joseph brought the money into Pharaoh\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And when the money was all spent in the land of Egypt and in the
        land of Canaan, all the Egyptians came to Joseph and said, \u201CGive us
        food. Why should we die before your eyes? For our money is gone.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And Joseph answered, \u201CGive your livestock, and I will give you
        food in exchange for your livestock, if your money is gone.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So they brought their livestock to Joseph, and Joseph gave them food
        in exchange for the horses, the flocks, the herds, and the donkeys. He supplied
        them with food in exchange for all their livestock that year. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And when that year was ended, they came to him the following year
        and said to him, \u201CWe will not hide from my lord that our money is all
        spent. The herds of livestock are my lord\u2019s. There is nothing left in
        the sight of my lord but our bodies and our land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Why should we die before your eyes, both we and our land? Buy us
        and our land for food, and we with our land will be servants to Pharaoh.
        And give us seed that we may live and not die, and that the land may not
        be desolate.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So Joseph bought all the land of Egypt for Pharaoh, for all the Egyptians
        sold their fields, because the famine was severe on them. The land became
        Pharaoh\u2019s. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'As for the people, he made servants of them[[COMMENT(0)]] from one
        end of Egypt to the other. '
      comments:
      - number: '47:21 '
        content: 'Samaritan, Septuagint, Vulgate; Hebrew '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Only the land of the priests he did not buy, for the priests had
        a fixed allowance from Pharaoh and lived on the allowance that Pharaoh gave
        them; therefore they did not sell their land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then Joseph said to the people, \u201CBehold, I have this day bought
        you and your land for Pharaoh. Now here is seed for you, and you shall sow
        the land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And at the harvests you shall give a fifth to Pharaoh, and four fifths
        shall be your own, as seed for the field and as food for yourselves and your
        households, and as food for your little ones.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And they said, \u201CYou have saved our lives; may it please my lord,
        we will be servants to Pharaoh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "So Joseph made it a statute concerning the land of Egypt, and it
        stands to this day, that Pharaoh should have the fifth; the land of the priests
        alone did not become Pharaoh\u2019s.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Thus Israel settled in the land of Egypt, in the land of Goshen.
        And they gained possessions in it, and were fruitful and multiplied greatly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And Jacob lived in the land of Egypt seventeen years. So the days
        of Jacob, the years of his life, were 147 years.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And when the time drew near that Israel must die, he called his son
        Joseph and said to him, \u201CIf now I have found favor in your sight, put
        your hand under my thigh and promise to deal kindly and truly with me. Do
        not bury me in Egypt, "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "but let me lie with my fathers. Carry me out of Egypt and bury me
        in their burying place.\u201D He answered, \u201CI will do as you have said.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And he said, \u201CSwear to me\u201D; and he swore to him. Then Israel
        bowed himself upon the head of his bed.[[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: '47:31 '
        content: 'Hebrew; Septuagint '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jacob Blesses Ephraim and Manasseh'
      title: Jacob Blesses Ephraim and Manasseh
      number: 1
      content: "  After this, Joseph was told, \u201CBehold, your father is ill.\u201D
        So he took with him his two sons, Manasseh and Ephraim. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And it was told to Jacob, \u201CYour son Joseph has come to you.\u201D
        Then Israel summoned his strength and sat up in bed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And Jacob said to Joseph, \u201CGod Almighty[[COMMENT(0)]] appeared
        to me at Luz in the land of Canaan and blessed me, "
      comments:
      - number: '48:3 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "and said to me, \u2018Behold, I will make you fruitful and multiply
        you, and I will make of you a company of peoples and will give this land
        to your offspring after you for an everlasting possession.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And now your two sons, who were born to you in the land of Egypt
        before I came to you in Egypt, are mine; Ephraim and Manasseh shall be mine,
        as Reuben and Simeon are. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the children that you fathered after them shall be yours. They
        shall be called by the name of their brothers in their inheritance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "As for me, when I came from Paddan, to my sorrow Rachel died in the
        land of Canaan on the way, when there was still some distance[[COMMENT(0)]]
        to go to Ephrath, and I buried her there on the way to Ephrath (that is,
        Bethlehem).\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '48:7 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "When Israel saw Joseph\u2019s sons, he said, \u201CWho are these?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Joseph said to his father, \u201CThey are my sons, whom God has given
        me here.\u201D And he said, \u201CBring them to me, please, that I may bless
        them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now the eyes of Israel were dim with age, so that he could not see.
        So Joseph brought them near him, and he kissed them and embraced them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And Israel said to Joseph, \u201CI never expected to see your face;
        and behold, God has let me see your offspring also.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then Joseph removed them from his knees, and he bowed himself with
        his face to the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Joseph took them both, Ephraim in his right hand toward Israel\u2019s
        left hand, and Manasseh in his left hand toward Israel\u2019s right hand,
        and brought them near him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Israel stretched out his right hand and laid it on the head of
        Ephraim, who was the younger, and his left hand on the head of Manasseh,
        crossing his hands (for Manasseh was the firstborn). '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And he blessed Joseph and said,\u201CThe God before whom my fathers
        Abraham and Isaac walked,the God who has been my shepherd all my life long
        to this day,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  the angel who has redeemed me from all evil, bless the boys;and
        in them let my name be carried on, and the name of my fathers Abraham and
        Isaac;and let them grow into a multitude[[COMMENT(0)]] in the midst of the
        earth.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '48:16 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "When Joseph saw that his father laid his right hand on the head of
        Ephraim, it displeased him, and he took his father\u2019s hand to move it
        from Ephraim\u2019s head to Manasseh\u2019s head. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Joseph said to his father, \u201CNot this way, my father; since
        this one is the firstborn, put your right hand on his head.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But his father refused and said, \u201CI know, my son, I know. He
        also shall become a people, and he also shall be great. Nevertheless, his
        younger brother shall be greater than he, and his offspring shall become
        a multitude[[COMMENT(0)]] of nations.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '48:19 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So he blessed them that day, saying,\u201CBy you Israel will pronounce
        blessings, saying,  \u2018God make you as Ephraim and as Manasseh.\u2019\u201DThus
        he put Ephraim before Manasseh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Israel said to Joseph, \u201CBehold, I am about to die, but
        God will be with you and will bring you again to the land of your fathers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Moreover, I have given to you rather than to your brothers one mountain
        slope[[COMMENT(0)]] that I took from the hand of the Amorites with my sword
        and with my bow.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '48:22 '
        content: 'Or ; Hebrew , which sounds like the town and district called '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jacob Blesses His Sons'
      title: Jacob Blesses His Sons
      number: 1
      content: "    Then Jacob called his sons and said, \u201CGather yourselves
        together, that I may tell you what shall happen to you in days to come.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CAssemble and listen, O sons of Jacob,listen to Israel your
        father.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CReuben, you are my firstborn,my might, and the firstfruits
        of my strength,preeminent in dignity and preeminent in power.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Unstable as water, you shall not have preeminence,because you went
        up to your father\u2019s bed;then you defiled it\u2014he went up to my couch!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "  \u201CSimeon and Levi are brothers;weapons of violence are their
        swords.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Let my soul come not into their council;  O my glory, be not joined
        to their company.For in their anger they killed men,and in their willfulness
        they hamstrung oxen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Cursed be their anger, for it is fierce,and their wrath, for it is
        cruel!I will divide them in Jacoband scatter them in Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CJudah, your brothers shall praise you;  your hand shall be
        on the neck of your enemies;  your father\u2019s sons shall bow down before
        you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Judah is a lion\u2019s cub;from the prey, my son, you have gone up. 
        He stooped down; he crouched as a lionand as a lioness; who dares rouse him?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The scepter shall not depart from Judah,nor the ruler\u2019s staff
        from between his feet,until tribute comes to him;[[COMMENT(0)]]and to him
        shall be the obedience of the peoples.  "
      comments:
      - number: '49:10 '
        content: 'By a slight revocalization; a slight emendation yields (compare
          Septuagint, Syriac, Targum) ; Hebrew , or '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Binding his foal to the vineand his donkey\u2019s colt to the choice
        vine,he has washed his garments in wineand his vesture in the blood of grapes.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'His eyes are darker than wine,and his teeth whiter than milk.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  \u201CZebulun shall dwell at the shore of the sea;he shall become
        a haven for ships,and his border shall be at Sidon.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "  \u201CIssachar is a strong donkey,crouching between the sheepfolds.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '49:14 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He saw that a resting place was good,and that the land was pleasant,so
        he bowed his shoulder to bear,and became a servant at forced labor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  \u201CDan shall judge his peopleas one of the tribes of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Dan shall be a serpent in the way,a viper by the path,that bites
        the horse\u2019s heelsso that his rider falls backward.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'I wait for your salvation, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "  \u201CRaiders shall raid Gad,[[COMMENT(0)]]but he shall raid at
        their heels.  "
      comments:
      - number: '49:19 '
        content: 'sounds like the Hebrew for and '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "  \u201CAsher\u2019s food shall be rich,and he shall yield royal
        delicacies.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "  \u201CNaphtali is a doe let loosethat bears beautiful fawns.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '49:21 '
        content: 'Or , or '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CJoseph is a fruitful bough,a fruitful bough by a spring;his
        branches run over the wall.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '49:22 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The archers bitterly attacked him,shot at him, and harassed him severely,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'yet his bow remained unmoved;his arms[[COMMENT(0)]] were made agileby
        the hands of the Mighty One of Jacob(from there is the Shepherd,  the Stone
        of Israel),  '
      comments:
      - number: '49:24 '
        content: 'Hebrew Or '
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  by the God of your father who will help you,by the Almighty[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        who will bless youwith blessings of heaven above,blessings of the deep that
        crouches beneath,blessings of the breasts and of the womb.  '
      comments:
      - number: '49:25 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The blessings of your fatherare mighty beyond the blessings of my
        parents,up to the bounties of the everlasting hills.[[COMMENT(0)]]May they
        be on the head of Joseph,and on the brow of him who was set apart from his
        brothers.  '
      comments:
      - number: '49:26 '
        content: 'A slight emendation yields (compare Septuagint) '
    - name: "27: Jacob\u2019s Death and Burial"
      title: "Jacob\u2019s Death and Burial"
      number: 27
      content: "  \u201CBenjamin is a ravenous wolf,in the morning devouring the
        preyand at evening dividing the spoil.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'All these are the twelve tribes of Israel. This is what their father
        said to them as he blessed them, blessing each with the blessing suitable
        to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then he commanded them and said to them, \u201CI am to be gathered
        to my people; bury me with my fathers in the cave that is in the field of
        Ephron the Hittite, "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'in the cave that is in the field at Machpelah, to the east of Mamre,
        in the land of Canaan, which Abraham bought with the field from Ephron the
        Hittite to possess as a burying place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "There they buried Abraham and Sarah his wife. There they buried Isaac
        and Rebekah his wife, and there I buried Leah\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "the field and the cave that is in it were bought from the Hittites.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: When Jacob finished commanding his sons, he drew up his feet into
        the bed and breathed his last and was gathered to his people.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "  Then Joseph fell on his father\u2019s face and wept over him and
        kissed him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Joseph commanded his servants the physicians to embalm his father.
        So the physicians embalmed Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Forty days were required for it, for that is how many are required
        for embalming. And the Egyptians wept for him seventy days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And when the days of weeping for him were past, Joseph spoke to the
        household of Pharaoh, saying, \u201CIf now I have found favor in your eyes,
        please speak in the ears of Pharaoh, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u2018My father made me swear, saying, \u201CI am about to die: in
        my tomb that I hewed out for myself in the land of Canaan, there shall you
        bury me.\u201D Now therefore, let me please go up and bury my father. Then
        I will return.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Pharaoh answered, \u201CGo up, and bury your father, as he made
        you swear.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So Joseph went up to bury his father. With him went up all the servants
        of Pharaoh, the elders of his household, and all the elders of the land of
        Egypt, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "as well as all the household of Joseph, his brothers, and his father\u2019s
        household. Only their children, their flocks, and their herds were left in
        the land of Goshen. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And there went up with him both chariots and horsemen. It was a very
        great company. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'When they came to the threshing floor of Atad, which is beyond the
        Jordan, they lamented there with a very great and grievous lamentation, and
        he made a mourning for his father seven days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "When the inhabitants of the land, the Canaanites, saw the mourning
        on the threshing floor of Atad, they said, \u201CThis is a grievous mourning
        by the Egyptians.\u201D Therefore the place was named Abel-mizraim;[[COMMENT(0)]]
        it is beyond the Jordan. "
      comments:
      - number: '50:11 '
        content: 'means (or ) '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Thus his sons did for him as he had commanded them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'for his sons carried him to the land of Canaan and buried him in
        the cave of the field at Machpelah, to the east of Mamre, which Abraham bought
        with the field from Ephron the Hittite to possess as a burying place. '
      comments: []
    - name: "14: God\u2019s Good Purposes"
      title: "God\u2019s Good Purposes"
      number: 14
      content: 'After he had buried his father, Joseph returned to Egypt with his
        brothers and all who had gone up with him to bury his father.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "When Joseph\u2019s brothers saw that their father was dead, they
        said, \u201CIt may be that Joseph will hate us and pay us back for all the
        evil that we did to him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So they sent a message to Joseph, saying, \u201CYour father gave
        this command before he died: "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u2018Say to Joseph, \u201CPlease forgive the transgression of your
        brothers and their sin, because they did evil to you.\u201D\u2019 And now,
        please forgive the transgression of the servants of the God of your father.\u201D
        Joseph wept when they spoke to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "His brothers also came and fell down before him and said, \u201CBehold,
        we are your servants.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But Joseph said to them, \u201CDo not fear, for am I in the place
        of God? "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'As for you, you meant evil against me, but God meant it for good,
        to bring it about that many people[[COMMENT(0)]] should be kept alive, as
        they are today. '
      comments:
      - number: '50:20 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '21: The Death of Joseph'
      title: The Death of Joseph
      number: 21
      content: "So do not fear; I will provide for you and your little ones.\u201D
        Thus he comforted them and spoke kindly to them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So Joseph remained in Egypt, he and his father\u2019s house. Joseph
        lived 110 years. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And Joseph saw Ephraim\u2019s children of the third generation. The
        children also of Machir the son of Manasseh were counted as Joseph\u2019s
        own.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '50:23 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And Joseph said to his brothers, \u201CI am about to die, but God
        will visit you and bring you up out of this land to the land that he swore
        to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Joseph made the sons of Israel swear, saying, \u201CGod will
        surely visit you, and you shall carry up my bones from here.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: So Joseph died, being 110 years old. They embalmed him, and he was
        put in a coffin in Egypt.
      comments: []
